ich%20to%20argue%20that%20it%20needs%20three%20and%20a%20half%20months%20more%2C%20pushing%20the%20deadline%20to%20June%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarg%20explained%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20simply%20asked%20for%20six%20simple%20bits%20of%20information%3A%20who%20purchased%20the%20bonds%2C%20the%20date%20and%20the%20amount%20and%20also%20which%20party%20received%20the%20bonds%2C%20when%20they%20were%20encashed%20and%20the%20amount.%20This%20information%20is%20readily%20available.%20The%20electoral%20bond%20guidelines%20of%202018%20themselves%20require%20that%20it%20should%20be%20given%20to%20any%20court%20when%20demanded%20and%20Justice%20Deepak%20Gupta%20has%20revealed%20that%20he%20was%20part%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20which%20in%202019%20ordered%20the%20bank%20to%20maintain%20such%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarg%20also%20said%20he%20believes%20that%20in%202019%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20sold%20up%20to%20that%20date%20were%20given%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20sealed%20envelope.%20At%20the%20time%20the%20bank%20did%20not%20need%20or%20ask%20for%20extra%20time.%20Why%20do%20they%20need%20extra%20time%20to%20give%20similar%20details%20for%20the%20period%20post%202019%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarg%20believes%20that%20by%20failing%20to%20meet%20the%20March%206%20deadline%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20is%20already%20guilty%20of%20contempt%20of%20court.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20has%20today%20filed%20a%20contempt%20case%20against%20the%20SBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHas%20this%20become%20a%20test%20case%20for%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20image%20and%20integrity%3F%20How%20embarrassed%20will%20the%20management%20of%20the%20SBI%20be%20today%3F%20What%20would%20be%20the%20impact%20if%20the%20bank%20is%20found%20guilty%20of%20contempt%3F%20Those%20are%20some%20of%20the%20other%20issues%20touched%20upon%20in%20this%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C