-fever-outbreak-europe%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParrot%20fever%2C%20caused%20by%20bacteria%20belonging%20to%20the%20Chlamydia%20family%2C%20is%20transmitted%20through%20various%20wild%20and%20domesticated%20birds%20and%20poultry.%20Infected%20birds%20may%20not%20exhibit%20symptoms%2C%20yet%20they%20can%20still%20shed%20the%20bacteria%20through%20breathing%20or%20excretion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fpneumonia%2Fatypical%2Fpsittacosis%2Findex.html%5C%22%3EUS%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20humans%20frequently%20contract%20parrot%20fever%20by%20inhaling%20dust%20particles%20contaminated%20with%20secretions%20from%20infected%20birds.%20Additionally%2C%20individuals%20can%20become%20ill%20if%20bitten%20by%20a%20bird%20or%20through%20direct%20contact%20between%20a%20bird's%20beak%20and%20a%20person's%20mouth.%20The%20disease%20does%20not%20spread%20through%20the%20consumption%20of%20infected%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20human-to-human%20transmission%20is%20possible%2C%20it%20is%20uncommon%2C%20as%20indicated%20by%20studies.%20In%20the%20majority%20of%20recent%20cases%2C%20individuals%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20infected%20domesticated%20or%20wild%20birds%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Femergencies%2Fdisease-outbreak-news%2Fitem%2F2024-DON509%5C%22%3EWorld%20Health%20Organization%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20individuals%20who%20contract%20parrot%20fever%20experience%20mild%20symptoms%2C%20typically%20appearing%20five%20to%2014%20days%20after%20exposure%20to%20an%20infected%20bird.%20These%20symptoms%20may%20include%20headache%2C%20muscle%20pain%2C%20dry%20cough%2C%20fever%2C%20and%20chills.%20Antibiotics%20are%20effective%20in%20treating%20the%20infection%2C%20and%20fatalities%20among%20humans%20are%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustria%2C%20which%20typically%20records%20two%20cases%20of%20the%20disease%20annually%2C%20reported%2014%20confirmed%20cases%20in%202023%20and%20an%20additional%20four%20cases%20this%20year%20as%20of%20March%204.%20These%20cases%20are%20unrelated%2C%20and%20none%20of%20the%20individuals%20reported%20travelling%20abroad%20or%20encountering%20wild%20birds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDenmark%20typically%20witnesses%2015%20to%2030%20human%20cases%20each%20year%2C%20with%20most%20stemming%20from%20contact%20with%20pet%20birds%20or%20hobby%20birds%20such%20as%20racing%20pigeons.%20As%20of%20February%2027%2C%20Denmark%20has%20confirmed%2023%20cases%20in%20this%20outbreak.%20However%2C%20public%20health%20officials%20suspect%20that%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20cases%20is%20considerably%20higher%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20Danish%20cases%2C%2017%20individuals%20have%20been%20hospitalized%2C%20with%2015%20diagnosed%20with%20pneumonia%2C%20and%20four%20fatalities%20have%20been%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Denmark%2C%20at%20least%20one%20person%20contracted%20parrot%20fever%20from%20a%20pet%20bird.%20Among%20the%2015%20other%20cases%20for%20which%20exposure%20information%20was%20available%2C%2012%20individuals%20reported%20contact%20with%20wild%20birds%2C%20mainly%20through%20bird%20feeders.%20Interestingly%2C%20three%20cases%20had%20no%20documented%20history%20of%20contact%20with%20birds%20of%20any%20type.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Germany%2C%20there%20were%2014%20confirmed%20cases%20of%20parrot%20fever%20in%202023%2C%20with%20an%20additional%20five%20cases%20reported%20this%20year.%20Nearly%20all%20affected%20individuals%20experienced%20pneumonia%2C%20with%2016%20requiring%20hospitalization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%2019%20cases%20in%20Germany%2C%20five%20individuals%20disclosed%20exposure%20to%20ill%20pet%20birds%20or%20chickens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202017%2C%20Sweden%20has%20witnessed%20a%20rise%20in%20parrot%20fever%20cases.%20Notably%2C%20in%20late%20November%20and%20early%20December%2C%20it%20recorded%20an%20unusually%20high%20number%20of%20cases%2C%20totalling%2026.%20However%2C%20this%20year%20has%20seen%20a%20decrease%20in%20cases%2C%20with%20only%2013%20reported%2C%20a%20lower%20figure%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20timeframe%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20Netherlands%20has%20experienced%20a%20surge%20in%20cases%2C%20registering%2021%20instances%20from%20late%20December%20through%20February%2029.%20This%20figure%20represents%20twice%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20recorded%20during%20the%20corresponding%20period%20in%20previous%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization.%20Typically%2C%20the%20Netherlands%20reports%20approximately%20nine%20cases%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWHO%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20monitor%20the%20outbreak.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709798280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fj84fs81_parrots-generic_625x300_07_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffatal-parrot-fever-outbreak-claims-5-lives-across-europe-5192832%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Parrot%20fever%2C%20caused%20by%20bacteria%20belonging%20to%20the%20Chlamydia%20family%2C%20is%20transmitted%20through%20various%20wild%20and%20domesticated%20birds%20and%20poultry.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffatal-parrot-fever-outbreak-claims-5-lives-across-europe-5192832%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffatal-parrot-fever-outbreak-claims-5-lives-across-europe-5192832%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffatal-parrot-fever-outbreak-claims-5-lives-across-europe-5192832%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2