%20Ravichandran%20Ashwin's%20voice%20trembled%20with%20emotion%20and%20pride%20during%20the%20gratitude-speech%20after%20receiving%20his%20special%20100th%20Test%20cap%20from%20India%20head%20coach%20Rahul%20Dravid%20here%20on%20Thursday.%20But%20Ashwin%20did%20not%20restrict%20that%20landmark%20moment%2C%20which%20came%20during%20the%20fifth%20and%20final%20Test%20against%20England%2C%20to%20himself%20but%20he%20championed%20the%20cause%20of%20Test%20cricket%20amidst%20money-spinning%20T20%20leagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIPL%20has%20been%20a%20hugely%20popular%20tournament%3B%20a%20lot%20of%20kids%20want%20to%20play%20T20%20and%20get%20into%20the%20IPL.%20I%20really%20do%20wish%20that%20they%20get%20there.%20But%20remember%20one%20thing%2C%20this%20format%20(Test)%E2%80%A6%20it%20is%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20life%20wouldn't%20teach%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Ashwin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20Test%20cricket%20is%20what%20life%20is.%20It%20is%20the%20closest%20synergy%20that%20you%20can%20find%20to%20life.%20It%20will%20teach%20you%20to%20adapt%2C%20dealing%20with%20pressures.%E2%80%9D%20The%2037-year-old%20Ashwin%2C%20who%20made%20his%20Test%20debut%20in%202011%2C%20also%20paid%20handsome%20tribute%20to%20his%20father%20--%20Ravichandran%20--%20for%20believing%20in%20him%20and%20supporting%20his%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt's%20quite%20an%20emotional%20moment.%20Not%20just%20not%20just%20for%20me.%20I'm%20not%20one%20who%20would%20be%20shaken%20by%20emotions%20a%20lot.%20But%20today%20is%20a%20hugely%20emotional%20moment%20for%20a%20man%20who%20is%20sitting%20back%20in%20Chennai.%20Unfortunately%2C%20he%20couldn't%20make%20it%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ashwin%20began%20before%20making%20a%20quick%20recollection%20of%20early%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20day%20(as%20a%20kid%20cricketer)%2C%20I%20still%20remember%20it%20very%20clearly%2C%20I%20would%20put%20my%20kit%20in%20front%20of%20the%20petrol%20tank%2C%20and%20then%20he%20would%20put%20me%20on%20the%20bike%20and%20take%20me%20to%20the%20coaching%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20government%20employee%20(his%20dad)%20wanted%20to%20take%20his%20son%20all%20the%20way%20miles%20ahead%20in%20life%2C%20somewhere%20he%20imagined%20I%20would%20ever%20get.%20He%20got%20me%20here%20because%20of%20the%20help%20of%20my%20mom%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20my%20granddad%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20wife%20Preeti%20has%20been%20a%20big%20pillar%20of%20support%20for%20him%20in%20periods%20of%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20wife%20didn't%20know%20what%20she%20was%20getting%20into.%20She's%20gotten%20into%20it%20and%20she's%20standing%20next%20to%20me%20today.%20I%20have%20got%20two%20lovely%20kids%20who%20are%20also%20enjoying%20my%20journey%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ashwin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20handing%20Ashwin%20the%20cap%2C%20Dravid%20said%20it%20was%20a%20well-deserved%20moment%20for%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20cricketer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20given%20everything%20faithfully%20to%20the%20team%20and%20today%20is%20your%20100th%20Test.%20It%20was%20a%20journey%20that%20started%20from%20the%20streets%20of%20Chennai.%20It's%20been%20a%20long%20and%20eventful%20journey.%20It%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20possible%20without%20your%20family.%20Congratulations%20to%20them%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20well-deserved%20moment.%20It's%20been%20a%20privilege%20speaking%20with%20you.%20It's%20been%20a%20privilege%20to%20work%20with%20you%20as%20a%20coach.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20it's%20a%20privilege%20to%20hand%20this%20cap%20to%20you%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dravid%20said%20amidst%20applause%20from%20Ashwin's%20teammates%2C%20who%20gave%20him%20a%20guard%20of%20honour%20while%20entering%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709792160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fq5d2il88_ashwin-and-prithi-bcci_625x300_07_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Findia-vs-england-2024%2Femotional-moment-for-a-man-sitting-in-chennai-r-ashwins-beautiful-tribute-to-dad-on-100th-test-5192189%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20handing%20Ravichandran%20Ashwin%20the%20cap%2C%20head%20coach%20Rahul%20Dravid%20said%20it%20was%20a%20well-deserved%20moment%20for%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20cricketer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Terrifying%20engine%20fire%20forces%20United%20Flight%20to%20abort%20trip%2C%20return%20to%20Houston%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709792016000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108288485%2Cimgsize-43372.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fterrifying-engine-fire-forces-united-flight-to-abort-trip-return-to-houston%2Farticleshow%2F108288292.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108288292.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20United%20Airlines%20Boeing%20aircraft%20was%20forced%20to%20make%20an%20emergency%20landing%20in%20Texas%20on%20Monday%2C%20just%20after%20takeoff%2C%20as%20flames%20erupted%20from%20one%20of%20its%20engines.%20Startling%20footage%20revealed%20vivid%20orange%20sparks%20emanating%20extensively%20from%20beneath%20the%20left%20wing%20of%20the%20plane%2C%20alarmingly%20close%20to%20the%20viewing%20windows%20of%20passengers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fterrifying-engine-fire-forces-united-flight-to-abort-trip-return-to-houston%2Farticleshow%2F108288292.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fterrifying-engine-fire-forces-united-flight-to-abort-trip-return-to-houston%2Famp_articleshow%2F108288292.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fterrifying-engine-fire-forces-united-flight-to-abort-trip-return-to-houston%2Famp_articleshow%2F108288292.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Supreme%20Court's%20Vote-For-Bribe%20Order%20Is%20Triumph%20Of%20Equality%2C%20Finally%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fc1l320oo_supreme-court-ani_625x300_23_February_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D1ctuUrauvEM%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESita%20Soren%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fno-immunity-to-mlas-mps-in-bribe-for-vote-cases-rules-supreme-court-766253%5C%22%3Eseven-judge%20Bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbribery-not-protected-by-parliamentary-privileges-supreme-court-5172474%5C%22%3Estated%20the%20obvious%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-explained-how-supreme-court-stripped-mps-mlas-of-immunity-in-bribery-cases-5173098%5C%22%3Ecourt%20said%20there%20is%20no%20immunity%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20legislator%20who%20accepts%20bribe%20for%20voting%20in%20Parliament.%20It%20overturned%20the%20earlier%20five-judge%20Bench%20ruling%20to%20the%20contrary%20in%20%3Cem%3EP%20V%20Narasimha%20Rao%20v.%20State%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1998)%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20'JMM%20Bribery%20case'.%20The%20court%20also%20said%20the%20offence%20is%20complete%20the%20moment%20illegal%20gratification%20is%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-on-no-immunity-to-mps-mlas-in-bribery-cases-salutary-judgement-5174264%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESita%20Soren%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fgreat-judgment-pm-s-post-on-no-immunity-to-mps-mlas-in-bribery-cases-766493%5C%22%3Eself-correction%20by%20the%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20something%20that%20was%20long%20overdue.%20It%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EP%20V%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20grants%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20to%20a%20member%20of%20a%20legislature%20who%20has%20allegedly%20engaged%20in%20bribery%20for%20casting%20a%20vote%20or%20speaking%2C%20has%20wide%20ramifications%20in%20public%20life%20and%20parliamentary%20democracy.%20There%20is%20a%20grave%20danger%20of%20this%20court%20allowing%20the%20error%20to%20be%20perpetuated%20if%20the%20decision%20were%20not%20reconsidered.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Older%20Split%20Verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20see%20the%20relevant%20constitutional%20provisions.%20Article%20105%20deals%20with%20the%20powers%20and%20privileges%20pertaining%20to%20Parliament%20and%20its%20members%2C%20and%20Article%20194%20deals%20with%20those%20of%20the%20state%20legislature%20and%20its%20members.%20They%20state%20that%20no%20member%20of%20the%20legislature%20%26quot%3Bshall%20be%20liable%20to%20any%20proceedings%20in%20any%20court%20in%20respect%20of%20anything%20said%20or%20any%20vote%20given%20by%20him%20in%20(the%20legislative%20body)%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EP%20V%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1998)%20was%20a%203%3A2%20verdict.%20The%20majority%20on%20the%20Bench%20had%20committed%20the%20folly%20of%20reading%20the%20constitutional%20provisions%20somewhat%20literally.%20Justice%20Learned%20Hand%20had%20famously%20said%20that%20there%20is%20no%20surer%20way%20to%20misread%20a%20document%20than%20to%20read%20it%20literally.%20That%20observation%20applies%20to%20the%20reading%20of%20the%20Constitution%20as%20well.%20More%20importantly%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ENarasimha%20Rao%20judgment%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20conceptually%20wrong%20when%20it%20said%20that%20a%20member%20of%20Parliament%20who%20obtains%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20in%20a%20particular%20way%20could%20still%20claim%20immunity%20from%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20105%20is%20thus%20literally%20read%2C%20understood%2C%20and%20invoked.%20The%20court%2C%20in%20the%201998%20verdict%2C%20said%20that%20a%20vote%20is%20an%20expression%2C%20which%2C%20nevertheless%2C%20is%20correct.%20In%20%3Cem%3EPeople's%20Union%20of%20Civil%20Liberties%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2003)%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20the%20right%20to%20make%20a%20choice%20by%20means%20of%20a%20ballot%20is%20part%20of%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20question%2C%20however%2C%20was%20not%20of%20voting%20per%20se.%20It%20was%20about%20the%20myth%20of%20constitutional%20protection%20claimed%20for%20an%20act%20of%20sheer%20corruption%20by%20the%20lawmaker.%20The%201998%20verdict%20was%20carried%20away%20by%20this%20myth%2C%20while%20the%20present%20ruling%20exposed%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterpreting%20Privileges%20And%20Their%20Victorian%20Roots%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliamentary%20privileges%20have%20a%20Victorian%20root.%20The%20British%20Parliament%20required%20the%20power%20to%20punish%20for%20contempt%20as%20it%20had%20the%20characteristics%20of%20a%20court%20as%20well.%20Its%20members%20also%20needed%20to%20speak%20freely%20and%20fearlessly%20without%20being%20intimidated%20by%20the%20Palace.%20In%20India%2C%20too%2C%20it%20might%20be%20understandable%20to%20protect%20a%20member's%20speech%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20legislative%20body%2C%20provided%20it%20does%20not%20amount%20to%20an%20offence.%20Yet%2C%20the%20position%20here%20is%20essentially%20different%20from%20that%20in%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20erroneous%20to%20think%20that%20constitutional%20interpretation%20is%20only%20a%20technical%20exercise%20based%20on%20the%20conventional%20tools%20of%20construction.%20It%20is%20an%20ethical%20process%20too.%20As%20such%2C%20it%20requires%20to%20be%20governed%20by%20the%20ethos%20of%20constitutional%20morality.%20In%20%3Cem%3EState%20(NCT%20of%20Delhi)%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2018)%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20quoted%20Justice%20Hand%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20meaning%20of%20a%20sentence%20may%20be%20more%20than%20that%20of%20the%20separate%20words%2C%20as%20a%20melody%20is%20more%20than%20the%20words.%26quot%3B%20The%20seven-judge%20Bench%20interpreted%20the%20articles%20and%20rightly%20said%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20constitutional%20provision%20is%20to%20protect%20the%20speech%20and%20not%20to%20protect%20an%20act%20that%20is%20otherwise%20an%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Importance%20Of%20Dissent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20verdict%20endorses%20the%20dissenting%20minority%20views%20rendered%20in%20the%20past%20on%20the%20subject.%20The%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Charles%20Evans%20Hughes%2C%20wrote%20that%20a%20dissent%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Ban%20appeal%20to%20the%20brooding%20spirit%20of%20law%2C%20to%20the%20intelligence%20of%20a%20future%20day%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20future%20is%20here.%20The%20future%20is%20reflected%20in%20%3Cem%3ESita%20Soren%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20master%20dissenter%2C%20Justice%20Subba%20Rao%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EM%20S%20M%20Sharma%20v.%20Shree%20Krishna%20Sinha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1960)%2C%20disagreed%20with%20the%20majority%20on%20the%20Bench%20and%20said%20that%20the%20legislature%20cannot%20torpedo%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20privilege.%20The%20minority%20view%20in%20%3Cem%3ENarasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E%20too%20has%20placed%20the%20dissent%20in%20perspective.%20It%20said%20that%20immunity%20for%20a%20Parliament%20member%20from%20criminal%20prosecution%20at%20the%20teeth%20of%20the%20allegation%20of%20voting%20based%20on%20bribery%20would%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20be%20repugnant%20to%20healthy%20functioning%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%20but%20would%20also%20be%20subversive%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%26quot%3B.%20But%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20not%20infallible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESC%20Sets%20A%20Useful%20Precedent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20judgment%20will%20set%20a%20useful%20precedent%20not%20only%20in%20bribery%20cases%20but%20in%20cases%20involving%20other%20offences%20too.%20To%20illustrate%2C%20on%20a%20proper%20extension%20of%20the%20logic%20of%20the%20present%20verdict%2C%20a%20lawmaker%20who%20commits%20a%20hate%20crime%20can%20no%20longer%20claim%20immunity.%20To%20take%20an%20example%2C%20Section%20153%20(A)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20punishes%20an%20act%20of%20%26quot%3Bpromoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%2C%20race%2C%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20residence%2C%20language%2C%20etc.%26quot%3B.%20Yet%2C%20many%20of%20our%20legislators%20could%20utter%20many%20things%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%20with%20impunity%2C%20even%20though%20such%20statements%20could%20attract%20penal%20provision%20if%20uttered%20outside%20the%20legislature%20or%20by%20an%20ordinary%20citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20applying%20the%20ratio%20of%20the%20present%20judgment%2C%20such%20a%20member%20can%20no%20longer%20claim%20immunity%20if%20what%20he%20said%20amounted%20to%20a%20hate%20crime%2C%20which%20could%20be%20different%20from%20hate%20speech%20simplicitor.%20Similar%20would%20be%20the%20position%20with%20respect%20to%20other%20offences.%20The%20current%20larger%20Bench%20has%20rightly%20referred%20to%20an%20earlier%20judgment%20written%20by%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20(as%20he%20then%20was)%2C%20where%20he%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bprivileges%20and%20immunities%20are%20not%20gateways%20to%20claim%20exemptions%20from%20the%20general%20law%20of%20the%20land%26quot%3B.%20That%20was%20a%20case%20against%20a%20few%20members%20of%20the%20Kerala%20Legislative%20Assembly%20who%20allegedly%20climbed%20over%20the%20Speaker's%20dais%20and%20caused%20damage%20to%20property%20in%20the%20assembly%20hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20Extended%20Discourse%20On%20Power%2C%20Immunity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20can%20also%20ignite%20a%20discourse%20on%20the%20desirability%20of%20retaining%20the%20privilege%20clauses%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Articles%20concerned%2C%20105%20and%20194%2C%C2%A0%C2%A0not%20only%20deal%20with%20immunity%20for%20members%20but%20also%20with%20the%20power%20of%20the%20legislature%20to%20punish%20for%20contempt.%20In%3Cem%3E%20State%20of%20Karnataka%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1977)%2C%20it%20was%20held%20that%20a%20house%20of%20Parliament%20or%20state%20legislature%20exercises%20a%20judicial%20or%20quasi-judicial%20function%20when%20it%20issues%20notice%20to%20a%20citizen%20alleging%20breach%20of%20privilege.%20Often%2C%20the%20outspoken%20public%20as%20well%20as%20the%20media%20have%20been%20proceeded%20against%20using%20this%20power.%20Attendance%20of%20such%20dissenters%20was%20insisted%20on%20several%20occasions%2C%20which%20did%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20freedom%20of%20expression%20for%20citizens%20in%20general%20and%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20good%20deal%20of%20judicial%20introspection%20about%20such%20power%20and%20privileges%20in%20India.%20It%20is%20now%20widely%20acknowledged%20that%20even%20in%20England%2C%20the%20judicial%20trend%20is%20against%20the%20idea%20of%20privilege.%20The%20importance%20of%20applying%20the%20%26quot%3Bnecessity%20test%26quot%3B%20was%20also%20emphasised%20by%20the%20top%20court%20earlier%2C%20which%20finds%20a%20reiteration%20in%20the%20present%20verdict%2C%20with%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople's%20March%20Over%20Political%20Feudalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20seven%20judges'%20ruling%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20enhance%20the%20level%20of%20freedom%20and%20probity%20in%20the%20country's%20personal%20and%20public%20life.%20It%20has%20a%20great%20equalising%20impact%20which%20places%20the%20citizens%20and%20their%20representatives%20on%20equal%20footing%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20penal%20laws.%20In%20%3Cem%3ERe%20S.Mulgaokar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1978)%2C%20Justice%20Krishna%20Iyer%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20court%20is%20not%20an%20inert%20abstraction%3B%20it%20is%20people%20in%20judicial%20power%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20verdict%20reflects%20people's%20march%20over%20political%20feudalism%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20privileges.%20It%20is%20a%20triumph%20of%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%20(stating%20equality%20before%20the%20law%20and%20equal%20protection%20by%20the%20laws)%20over%20the%20medieval%20notion%20of%20privilege%2C%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20which%20in%20a%20modern%20democracy%20is%20very%20much%20questionable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kaleeswaram%20Raj%20is%20a%20lawyer%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709791920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fc5p4n3lg_supreme-court-premises_625x300_22_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsupreme-courts-vote-for-bribe-order-is-a-triumph-of-equality-5192282%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court's%20verdict%20reflects%20people's%20march%20over%20political%20feudalism%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20privileges.%20It%20is%20a%20triumph%20of%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%20over%20the%20medieval%20notion%20of%20privilege.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsupreme-courts-vote-for-bribe-order-is-a-triumph-of-equality-5192282%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsupreme-courts-vote-for-bribe-order-is-a-triumph-of-equality-5192282%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsupreme-courts-vote-for-bribe-order-is-a-triumph-of-equality-5192282%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22General%20Elections%20Buzz%3A%20What%E2%80%99s%20Happening%20in%20Odisha%20and%20Maharashtra%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07113917%2FGH6wOEuWIAAUNNt.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaharashtra%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fbjp-faces-stiff-challenge-from-allies-shiv-sena-and-ncp-in-wrangle-over-48-lok-sabha-seats-in-maharashtra%2Farticle67921656.ece%5C%22%3ENewspaper%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20cited%20%E2%80%9Ca%20grievance%20letter%20posted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20on%20March%204%20as%20providing%20an%20insight%20into%20the%20tussle%20within%20the%20ruling%20Mahayuti%20alliance.%20The%20Shiv%20Sena%20(Shinde)%20is%20demanding%2022%20seats%2C%20the%20NCP%20(Ajit%20Pawar)%20has%20staked%20claim%20to%20at%20least%2010%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20wants%20%E2%80%9Cat%20least%2030%20seats%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20letter%20from%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20Harshavardhan%20Patil%20to%20party%20colleague%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20alluded%20to%20a%20%E2%80%98sinister%E2%80%99%20political%20campaign%20by%20NCP%20workers%20in%20Indapur%2C%20one%20of%20the%20six%20assembly%20constituencies%20that%20make%20up%20the%20Baramati%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20I%20am%20working%20under%20your%20leadership%20in%20the%20political%20and%20social%20spheres%20in%20my%20taluk%2C%20some%20office-bearers%20from%20our%20allied%20parties%20are%20making%20objectionable%20statements%20against%20me%20in%20public%20rallies%20in%20Indapur%2C%20using%20foul%20language.%20I%20am%20worried%20about%20my%20safety%20as%20they%20are%20threatening%20not%20to%20allow%20me%20to%20roam%20around%20Indapur%20during%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20stated%20the%20letter%2C%20urging%20Fadnavis%20to%20take%20%E2%80%9Ca%20firm%20stand%E2%80%9D%20to%20nip%20%E2%80%9Chooligan%20tendencies%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20bud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mid-day.com%2Fmumbai%2Fmumbai-news%2Farticle%2Famit-shah-urges-maharashtra-bjp-to-secure-all-48-lok-sabha-seats-23338496%5C%22%3EA%20%3Cem%3EMid-day%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20page%20one%20anticipates%20a%20clean%20run%20for%20the%20BJP%20in%20seat-sharing%20talks%2C%20with%20fighting%20the%20maximum%20ever%2C%20around%20%E2%80%9C34-35%20of%20the%2048%20seats.%E2%80%9D%20It%20reports%20that%20Amit%20Shah%20may%20have%20spooked%20the%20truncated%20Shiv%20Sena%20(Eknath%20Shinde)%20and%20truncated%20NCP%20(Ajit%20Pawar)%20into%20believing%20that%20their%20popularity%20stands%20diminished%20having%20left%20the%20founder%E2%80%99s%20parties%20respectively%20and%20walked%20off%20and%20joined%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShinde%20and%20Ajit%20Pawar%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cflexing%20their%20muscle%E2%80%9D%20as%20of%20late%2C%20wanting%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20that%20their%20undivided%20parties%20contested%20last%20time%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20the%20BJP%20wants%20to%20maximise%20its%20own%20numbers.%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20is%20cited%20as%20saying%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmedia%E2%80%9D%20must%20not%20indulge%20in%20%E2%80%9Ckite%20flying%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%23WireTake%3A%20Maharashtra%20is%20very%20tricky%20for%20the%20BJP.%20This%20is%20where%20the%20party%20has%20tried%20twice%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20and%20not%20via%20elections%2C%20to%20wrest%20power%2C%20once%20unsuccessfully%20when%20Ajit%20Pawar%20went%20back%20after%20being%20sworn%20in%2C%20but%20the%20second%20time%20successfully%20when%20Shinde%20and%20hordes%20of%20MLAs%20were%20flown%20to%20Guwahati%20and%20the%20regime%20toppled.%20There%20is%2C%20though%2C%20no%20electoral%20reckoning%20yet%20of%20what%20has%20happened.%20Bombay%20municipal%20elections%20have%20been%20on%20hold%20and%20Maharashtra%20has%20earned%20the%20dubious%20record%20of%20not%20having%20a%20single%20elected%20official.%20The%20%3C%2Fem%3EHindustan%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fmumbai-news%2Fwhy-does-maharashtra-not-have-a-single-elected-municipal-body-101704314173475.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ereported%20on%20January%204%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%9Cas%202023%20drew%20to%20a%20close%2C%20so%20did%20the%20terms%20of%20two%20of%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20municipal%20corporations%20%E2%80%94%20Ahmednagar%20and%20Dhule.%20These%20were%20the%20last%20two%20local%20bodies%20with%20elected%20officials.%20As%20of%20today%2C%20there%20is%20not%20a%20single%20elected%20body%20in%20all%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%2027%20municipal%20corporations.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20total%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20a%20whopping%C2%A0%E2%82%B91%2C10%2C556%20crore%20%E2%80%94%20is%20under%20the%20indirect%20control%20of%20the%20state%20government%20through%20its%20appointed%20%E2%80%98administrators%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOdisha%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20accusing%20each%20other%20of%20spreading%20%E2%80%9Crumours%E2%80%9D%20of%20an%20alliance%2C%20speculation%20over%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20ruling%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20%E2%80%9Cforging%20a%20formal%20alliance%20for%20the%20coming%20elections%E2%80%9D%20was%20back%20on%20the%20table%20with%20many%20newspaper%20reports%20with%20details%20on%20what%20may%20be%20going%20on.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Flok-sabha%2Fbjd-bjp-hold-talks-at-their-own-levels-for-forging-formal-alliance%2Farticle67921625.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20both%20parties%20on%20Wednesday%20%E2%80%9Cheld%20hectic%20deliberations%20at%20their%20own%20levels%20to%20smoothen%20rough%20edges.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20side%20came%20out%20with%20a%20statement%20giving%20any%20clarity%20on%20the%20proposed%20alliance.%20After%20a%20three%20and%20a%20half%20hour-long%20meeting%20of%20senior%20BJD%20leaders%20at%20the%20residence%20of%20Odisha%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik%2C%20there%20appear%20to%20be%20enough%20indications%20about%20formal%20alliance%20clicking.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20discussions%2C%20it%20was%20resolved%20that%20since%20by%202036%2C%20Odisha%20will%20complete%20100%20years%20of%20its%20statehood%20and%20the%20BJD%20and%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20have%20major%20milestones%20to%20be%20achieved%20by%20this%20time%2C%20therefore%20the%20BJD%20will%20do%20everything%20towards%20this%20in%20the%20greater%20interests%20of%20people%20of%20Odisha%20and%20the%20State%2C%E2%80%9D%20BJD%20vice-president%20Debi%20Prasad%20Mishra%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20Former%20Union%20tribal%20affairs%20minister%20Jual%20Oram%20is%20reported%20as%20saying%20the%20state%20unit%20of%20the%20BJP%20had%20proposed%20to%20go%20it%20alone%20in%20the%20elections%20%E2%80%9Cbut%2C%20it%20was%20up%20to%20the%20Central%20leadership%20to%20take%20a%20final%20call.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%23WireTake%3A%20This%2C%20if%20it%20happens%20would%20mean%20BJD%20teaming%20up%20with%20BJP%20after%20a%20gap%20of%2015%20years.%20This%20may%20leave%20the%20Congress%20as%20the%20sole%20significant%20opposition%20party%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20party%E2%80%99s%20turnaround%20in%20Telangana%2C%20where%20rumours%20of%20a%20hidden%20alliance%20between%20the%20ruling%20BRS%20and%20BJP%20had%20helped%20it%20storm%20to%20power%2C%20has%20created%20tension%20on%20the%20east%20coast%20where%20each%20state%20has%20a%20local%20regional%20party%20with%20an%20ambiguous%20relationship%20with%20the%20BJP.%20BJD%20formalising%20its%20ties%20so%20close%20to%20the%20general%20elections%20would%20make%20it%20a%20clear%20contest%20for%20the%20Congress%20to%20make%20gains%20in.%20BJP-BJD%20may%20be%20calculating%20the%20reverse%2C%20as%20one%20where%20they%20can%20dominate%20the%20discourse%20completely%20by%20coming%20together.%20BJP%20has%20eight%20seats%20of%20the%2021%20seats%20in%20the%20state.%20State%20polls%20will%20also%20be%20held%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709791871000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07113917%2FGH6wOEuWIAAUNNt.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgeneral-elections-buzz-whats-happening-in-odisha-and-maharashtra%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20a%20BJD-BJP%20alliance%20in%20the%20offing%3F%20Will%20it%20help%20or%20hurt%20the%20ruling%20parties%20facing%20decades-long%20anti-incumbency%3F%20What%20is%20holding%20up%20Maharashtra%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgeneral-elections-buzz-whats-happening-in-odisha-and-maharashtra%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tipra%20Motha%20Set%20to%20Join%20BJP-led%20Govt%20in%20Tripura%2C%20Likely%20to%20Get%20Two%20Cabinet%20Berths%22%2C%22content