%20so%20much%20money%20off%20oil%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20extra%20revenue%20Russia%20raised%20in%20February%20came%20from%20higher%20taxes%20on%20domestic%20oil%20producers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20already%20had%20a%20mechanism%20in%20place%20that%20would%20allow%20it%20to%20tax%20oil%20producers%20at%20a%20higher%20rate%2C%20it%20just%20wasn't%20using%20it.%20Russia%20applied%20the%20price%20floor%20for%20January%20oil%20sales%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20started%20receiving%20those%20taxes%20in%20February%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-03-01%2Frussia-uses-price-floor-to-protect-government-oil-revenue-from-sanctions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20on%20Friday%2C%20citing%20a%20letter%20from%20Russia's%20Federal%20Tax%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow's%20decision%20to%20activate%20the%20price%20floor%20came%20after%20the%20price%20of%20Russia's%20flagship%20Urals%20crude%20fell%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Fenforcement-g7-price-cap-hitting-russian-oil-prices-us-treasury-official-2024-01-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etougher%20sanctions%20enforcement%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20an%20energy%20major%2C%20with%20one-third%20of%20its%20revenue%20coming%20from%20oil%20and%20gas.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20European%20Union%2C%20Russia's%20single%20largest%20customer%20before%20the%20war%2C%20has%20spent%20the%20past%20two%20years%20trying%20to%20wean%20itself%20off%20Russian%20oil%20and%20gas%20to%20squeeze%20the%20Kremlin's%20war%20chest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20G7-led%20price%20cap%20of%20%2460%20a%20barrel%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fg7-countries-price-cap-russian-oil-moscow-vows-cut-off-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20helped%20keep%20a%20lid%20on%20prices%20and%20the%20Kremlin's%20oil%20revenues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20G7's%20restrictions%20don't%20restrict%20anyone%20from%20buying%20the%20products%20as%20long%20as%20they%20don't%20use%20Western%20insurance%20and%20shipping%20services%2C%20and%20Moscow%20has%20managed%20to%20pivot%20its%20customer%20base%20eastward%20toward%20countries%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-divert-oil-exports-europe-india-china-circumvent-sanctions-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%20and%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20also%20managed%20to%20get%20around%20the%20price%20cap%20and%20sanctions%20by%20using%20a%20huge%20%26quot%3Bdark%26quot%3B%20fleet%20of%20aging%20ships%20and%20by%20using%20intermediaries%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Frussian-oil-laundered-china-india-moscow-sanctions-europe-west-ukraine-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Blaunder%26quot%3B%20its%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EElections%20coming%20up%20this%20month%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20is%20tightening%20trade%20restrictions%20against%20Russia%20to%20force%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20halt%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20US%20and%20EU%20are%20imposing%20controversial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-biggest-banks-stop-russia-payments-icbc-ccb-boc-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecondary%20sanctions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20companies%20outside%20their%20legal%20jurisdictions%20to%20force%20compliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moves%20are%20keeping%20Russia%20on%20its%20toes%3A%20The%20Kremlin's%20spokesperson%2C%20Dmitry%20Peskov%2C%20admitted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barrons.com%2Fnews%2Frussia-admits-problems-with-china-payments-1d9e5887%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissues%20with%20Chinese%20bank%20transactions%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20government%20n