en%20were%20the%20primary%20%E2%80%98gatherers%E2%80%99%20and%20plant%20specialists%2C%20providing%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20food%20and%20medicine.%20By%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5120854%2F%5C%22%3E21%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20BCE%2C%20those%20of%20the%20Levant%20knew%20well%20the%20produce%20of%20their%20coastal%20woodlands%20and%20neighbouring%20steppelands%2C%20which%20stretched%20eastward%20for%20hundreds%20of%20kilometres.%20At%20least%20two%20common%20steppe%20grasses%2C%20wheat%20and%20barley%20(%3Cem%3Ejau%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20produced%20tasty%2C%20nutritionally-dense%20seeds.%20Using%20long%2C%20thin%2C%20flint%20blades%2C%20they%20gathered%20these%20grasses%20by%20the%20armload.%20In%20their%20small%20encampments%2C%20they%20threshed%20out%20short%20mounds%20of%20seeds%20and%20ground%20these%20with%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlongside%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20varieties%20of%20other%20plants%20they%20gathered%20nearby%2C%20plus%20meat%20from%20hunting%2C%20this%20grain%20provided%20an%20astonishing%2C%20almost%20effortless%20surplus%20from%20their%20cold%2C%20arid%20landscape.%20Even%20with%20the%20world%20in%20the%20grip%20of%20extreme%20glaciation%2C%20it%20was%20enough%20for%20their%20small%20bands%20to%20remain%20stationary%20for%20most%20of%20the%20year%E2%80%94the%20first%20multi-seasonal%20camps%20we%20know%20of%2C%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%20But%20eventually%20the%20nomads%20moved%20on%2C%20leaving%20behind%20their%20heavy%20mortars%20to%20be%20found%20and%20reused%20in%20future%20years%2C%20if%20the%20grasses%20grew%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20458px)%2085vw%2C%20458px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105051%2FStone_Age_Stone_Mortar__Pestle_Kebaran_culture_22000-18000_BP.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105051%2FStone_Age_Stone_Mortar__Pestle_Kebaran_culture_22000-18000_BP.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105051%2FStone_Age_Stone_Mortar__Pestle_Kebaran_culture_22000-18000_BP-300x298.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105051%2FStone_Age_Stone_Mortar__Pestle_Kebaran_culture_22000-18000_BP-1024x1018.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105051%2FStone_Age_Stone_Mortar__Pestle_Kebaran_culture_22000-18000_BP-150x150.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700532%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22455%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKebaran%20mortar%20and%20pestle%2C%20dating%20from%2022%E2%80%9318%20thousand%20years%20ago.%20The%20Israel%20Museum%2C%20Jerusalem%20Archaeology.%20Photo%3A%20Gary%20Todd%2FPublic%20domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20opportunistic%20trysts%20with%20wild%20grain%20would%20take%20some%2015%2C000%20years%20to%20develop%20into%20the%20kind%20of%20intensive%2C%20fixed-field%20agriculture%20needed%20to%20support%20a%20city%2C%20and%20another%204%2C000%20years%20to%20take%20over%20the%20world.%20Indeed%2C%20this%20%E2%80%98Agricultural%20Revolution%2C%E2%80%99%20regularly%20presented%20as%20a%20grand%20origin%20myth%20of%20modern%20civilisation%2C%20was%20neither%20a%20swift%20nor%20serendipitous%20innovation%20eagerly%20embraced%20by%20all.%20Nor%20would%20it%20herald%20a%20giant%20leap%20in%20the%20social%2C%20healthful%2C%20and%20creative%20prospects%20of%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%209000%20BCE%2C%20in%20the%20significantly%20warmer%2C%20wetter%20conditions%20of%20the%20early%20Holocene%2C%20lush%20grasslands%20shimmered%20from%20the%20expanding%20Levantine%20woodlands%20toward%20the%20eastern%20horizon.%20Foragers%20living%20there%20and%20in%20southern%20Anatolia%20now%20relied%20upon%20more%20regular%20and%20abundant%20grass%20harvests.%20Some%20of%20them%20had%20even%20settled%20into%20permanent%20villages%20of%20two%20or%20three%20thousand%20people%20living%20in%20tightly%20packed%20clusters%20of%20unbaked-brick%20houses.%20Their%20sickles%20were%20now%20more%20refined%20and%20they%20stored%20their%20heaps%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs00334-023-00945-x%5C%22%3Egrain%20in%20vessels%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20resist%20the%20teeming%20mice%2C%20drawn%20to%20the%20easy%20food%20found%20in%20the%20first%20human%20settlements.%20Cooks%20had%20already%20invented%20new%20techniques%20and%20recipes%20particular%20to%20cereals%3A%20Mix%20and%20mash%20warmed%2C%20malted%20grains%2C%20then%20add%20water%20and%20leave%20the%20brew%20until%20it%20bubbles%20into%20a%20thin%2C%20yeasty%20porridge%E2%80%94a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.stanford.edu%2Fpress-releases%2F2018%2F09%2F12%2Fcrafting-beer-lereal-cultivation%2F%5C%22%3Eprecursor%20of%20beer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Grind%20wheat%20into%20flour%2C%20then%20moisten%20and%20mix%20it%20into%20a%20dough%20and%20throw%20it%20onto%20the%20fire%2C%20until%20it%20bakes%20into%20bread.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20precise%20timeline%20of%20agriculture%20in%20South%20Asia%20remains%20largely%20unknown%2C%20due%20to%20paucity%20of%20early%20archaeological%20remains.%20But%20evidence%20suggests%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS1040618211002989%5C%22%3Eearliest%20Indian%20cultivators%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20forest%20nomads%20who%E2%80%94for%20unknown%20millennia%E2%80%94burned%20small%20plots%20(%3Cem%3Eswidden%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Ejhum%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20to%20grow%20legumes%20for%20a%20season%2C%20then%20fallowed%20those%20gardens%20for%20decades%2C%20re-wilding%20the%20swidden%20as%20forest.%20Over%20millennia%2C%20they%20incorporated%20browntop%20millet%20(%3Cem%3Eandakorra%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3ETelugu)%20and%20other%20native%20plants%20into%20their%20evolving%20swidden%20systems.%20They%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F345827627_Early_agriculture_in_South_Asia%5C%22%3Epracticed%20arboriculture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20domesticating%20mangos%2C%20citron%2C%20even%20entire%20teak%20forests%2C%20beginning%20unknown%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVillagers%20also%20foraged%20other%20wild%20foods%20to%20supply%20half%20of%20their%20diet.%20But%2C%20instead%20of%20following%20migrating%20herds%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwwnorton.com%2Fcollege%2Farchaeology%2Fhumanpast%2Fsummaries%2Fch06.html%5C%22%3Esemi-settled%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.1113931109%5C%22%3Efully-settled%20foragers%3C%2Fa%3E%20focused%20more%20on%20fishing%20and%20trapping%20smaller%2C%20non-migratory%20animals%E2%80%94hares%2C%20turtles%2C%20birds%2C%20and%20suchlike%E2%80%94from%20nearby.%20Having%20once%20consumed%20a%20much%20broader%20range%20of%20plants%20and%20animals%20across%20different%20habitats%20as%20they%20roamed%2C%20now%20they%20had%20only%20what%20was%20seasonally%20available%20in%20their%20fixed%20vicinity.%20As%20this%20likely%20increased%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs00334-023-00917-1%5C%22%3Edependency%20upon%20stored%20grain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20tended%20and%20managed%20the%20nearby%20grasslands%2C%20promoting%20the%20abundant%20growth%20of%20their%20favored%20grasses%20within%20the%20extant%20ecosystem.%20But%20feeding%20ever%20more%20mouths%20from%20a%20fixed%20location%20was%20still%20risky.%20Productivity%20depended%20entirely%20upon%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20486px)%2085vw%2C%20486px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105220%2FNatufian-woman.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22486%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105220%2FNatufian-woman.jpg%20720w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07105220%2FNatufian-woman-240x300.jpg%20240w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700533%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22608%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EArtist%E2%80%99s%20depiction%20of%20a%20Natufian%20gatherer-hunter%2C%2012.5%E2%80%9310%20thousand%20years%20ago%2C%20with%20jewelry%20based%20on%20archaeological%20finds%20from%20El%20Wad%20in%20what%20is%20now%20Israel.%20Photo%3A%20Brandon%20Spilcher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%207000%20BCE%20fully%20settled%20forager-gardeners%20across%20Anatolia%20were%20also%20growing%20peas%2C%20chickpeas%2C%20flax%2C%20and%20a%20few%20other%20species%20in%20their%20communal%20wheat%20and%20barley%20fields%2C%20where%20they%20broke%20the%20soil%20for%20more%20invasive%20planting.%20This%20caused%20%E2%80%98weeds%E2%80%99%20also%20to%20spread%2C%20but%20these%20ultimately%20helped%20to%20maintain%20soil%20health%2C%20fix%20nitrogen%2C%20and%20resist%20blight.%20Birds%20and%20bugs%20and%20other%20animals%20ate%20some%20of%20their%20produce.%20They%20also%20contributed%20fertiliser%2C%20helped%20pollinate%2C%20and%20aerated%20the%20soil.%20But%20to%20get%20more%20fertiliser%20for%20their%20gardens%20and%20more%20meat%20in%20their%20diets%2C%20some%20communities%20experimented%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs12520-019-00988-0%5C%22%3Epenning%20pigs%20or%20goats%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20villages%2C%20the%20first%20domesticated%20%E2%80%98livestock.%E2%80%99%20All%20this%20made%20for%20heavier%20work%20than%20their%20nomadic%20ancestors%20had%20done%2C%20but%20they%20still%20did%20it%20communally%2C%20innovating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fcambridge-archaeological-journal%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fstaying-egalitarian-and-the-origins-of-agriculture-in-the-middle-east%2FD3C1DBFE86DDA9D5B42BA219723175EE%5C%22%3Esocial%20institutions%20and%20ritual%20practices%20intended%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20maintain%20what%20archaeologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstanfordmag.org%2Fcontents%2Fwhat-happened-here%5C%22%3EIan%20Hodder%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20called%20their%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fanatolian-studies%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fcatalhoyuk-the-leopard-changes-its-spots-a-summary-of-recent-work%2FF08BEF691662478E9D85A59A8A93E307%5C%22%3Eaggressively%20egalitarian%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fprogrammes%2Farticles%2F4vD023dn4cp8wF2lRntcQ7L%2Fis-gender-inequality-man-made%5C%22%3Esociopolitical%20structure%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20this%20manner%20of%20sedentary%20abundance%2C%20they%20were%20having%20more%20children%20compared%20to%20nomadic%20peoples%2C%20who%20prefer%20to%20space%20children%20several%20years%20apart%20(since%20they%20must%20carry%20them).%20With%20higher%20birth%20rates%2C%20villages%20of%20Anatolian%20gardeners%20mushroomed%20and%20multiplied%2C%20expanding%20across%20the%20Bosphorus%2C%20following%20along%20river%20courses%20that%20would%20lead%20them%20over%20the%20next%20thousands%20of%20years%20into%20Central%20Europe.%20Some%20were%20also%20crossing%20the%20Mediterranean%2C%20stepwise%20by%20simple%20watercraft%2C%20colonising%20the%20previously%20uninhabited%20Cyclades%20Islands%20and%20Crete%2C%20eventually%20reaching%20the%20Peloponnese%20peninsula.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20carried%20their%20crops%20and%20animals%20to%20their%20new%20lands%2C%20maybe%20leaning%20more%20heavily%20upon%20farming%2C%20less%20upon%20foraging%20in%20increasingly%20unfamiliar%20territories.%20And%20as%20they%20went%2C%20they%20displaced%20the%20nomadic%20foraging%20populations%20of%20Europe.%20Only%20along%20the%20Nile%20River%20and%20in%20Mesopotamia%2C%20between%20the%20Tigris%20and%20Euphrates%20Rivers%2C%20were%20the%20local%20peoples%20attracted%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20growing%20grain%20themselves.%20Here%20many%20foraging%20communities%20were%20already%20living%20in%20fully%20or%20semi-settled%20villages.%20Their%20well-watered%20regions%20in%20the%20warm%20climate%20were%20so%20richly%20abundant%20that%20the%20grains%20would%20merely%20be%20a%20bonus%E2%80%94at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommunities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fdry-lake-bed-throws-up-new-facts-on-ganga-plain%2Fcid%2F806189%5C%22%3Einhabiting%20grasslands%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20the%20Gangetic%20plains%20were%20already%20promoting%20the%20abundance%20of%20native%20wild%20cereals%20before%2013%2C000%20BCE%2C%20hinting%20at%20multi-millennial%20domestication%20paths%20for%20millets%20and%20rices%20in%20the%20subcontinent.%20However%2C%20these%20communities%20didn%E2%80%99t%20build%20dense%20urban%20settlements.%20Rather%2C%20South%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20first%20towns%20arose%20in%20the%20Indus%20Valley%2C%20from%203300%20BCE%2C%20founded%20upon%20wheat%2C%20barley%2C%20and%20cattle.%20Those%20grains%20were%20probably%20carried%20into%20the%20subcontinent%20by%20goat%20pastoralists%20migrating%20from%20further%20west%20well%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9273075%2F%5C%22%3Ebefore%207000%20BCE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20prior%20to%20local%20cattle%20domestication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20in%20lifestyle%E2%80%94sedentism%2C%20brick%20making%2C%20farming%2C%20and%20other%20novel%20experiences%E2%80%94cascaded%20into%20dramatic%20changes%20in%20how%20people%20spent%20their%20time%2C%20how%20they%20structured%20their%20social%20ties%20and%20ritual%20lives%2C%20how%20they%20assigned%20value%20to%20people%2C%20ideas%2C%20activities%2C%20and%20things.%20Their%20stories%20of%20themselves%2C%20their%20cosmologies%20of%20meaning%2C%20transformed%20to%20reflect%20these%20changes.%20Mesopotamians%20would%20eventually%20develop%20the%20first%20linguistic%20writing%20system.%20And%20the%20peoples%20of%20the%20Fertile%20Crescent%20would%20leave%20behind%20the%20oldest%20surviving%20written%20tales%2C%20which%20became%20a%20primary%20source%20of%20the%20cultural%20narratives%20that%20continue%20to%20dominate%20the%20world%20up%20until%20the%20present%20day%20(more%20on%20this%20ahead).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20329px)%2085vw%2C%20329px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22329%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22452%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrass%20seed%20cultivation%20in%20Mesopotamia%20remained%20easy%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Settled%20villagers%20had%20only%20to%20toss%20some%20seeds%20on%20the%20seasonally%20renewed%2C%20deltaic%20floodplains%2C%20while%20they%20continued%20to%20fish%20and%20gather%20wild%20plants%20and%20small%20animals.%20Nomadic%20pastoralists%20of%20the%20region%20could%20also%20spread%20these%20grasses%20even%20while%20continuing%20their%20seasonal%20migrations%20with%20their%20goats.%20Given%20this%20easy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DIpGwdfX3zms%5C%22%3Esurplus%20of%20food%2C%20the%20settled%20populations%20swelled%3C%2Fa%3E%20beyond%20anything%20anyone%20had%20ever%20seen%20before%3B%20new%20settlements%20cropped%20up%20left%20and%20right%20across%20the%20delta.%20By%204000%20BCE%2C%20a%20Mesopotamian%20town%20might%20house%20upwards%20of%20fifteen%20thousand%20souls%E2%80%94among%20the%20largest%20clustered%20populations%20in%20the%20world%2C%20when%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20still%20lived%20as%20nomads.%20But%20all%20that%20easy%20grain%20no%20longer%20stretched%20as%20far.%20Fishing%2C%20trapping%2C%20and%20other%20subsistence%20activities%20were%20also%20proving%20inadequate%2C%20as%20the%20landscape%20was%20picked%20clean%20sooner%20each%20season.%20Resources%20that%20took%20more%20time%20to%20replenish%2C%20like%20firewood%2C%20were%20becoming%20scarce.%20Mice%20were%20becoming%20major%20pests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETownsfolk%20could%20spread%20more%20seeds%20over%20larger%20areas%2C%20but%20merely%20expanding%20this%20simple%20method%20gave%20diminishing%20returns.%20Out%20of%20necessity%2C%20they%20began%20to%20cut%20down%20the%20surrounding%20forests%20for%20firewood%2C%20further%20driving%20off%20the%20animals%20upon%20whom%20they%E2%80%99d%20relied%20for%20meat%2C%20whose%20antlers%2C%20bones%2C%20claws%2C%20sinews%2C%20and%20other%20parts%20they%20used%20for%20their%20tools%20and%20adornments.%20Deforestation%20also%20altered%20the%20rivers%E2%80%99%20patterns%20of%20siltation%20and%20erosion%2C%20leaving%20their%20fields%20and%20settlements%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20inundations.%20In%20attempting%20to%20continue%20their%20way%20of%20life%20with%20more%20and%20more%20people%2C%20they%20were%20destroying%20local%20forests%20and%20wetlands.%20They%20were%20beginning%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Eovershoot%20the%20carrying%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20local%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20built%20watercraft%20to%20help%20them%20harvest%20trees%20further%20upriver%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20run%20out%20of%20wood%2C%20but%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20flow%20became%20increasingly%20unpredictable%20and%20the%20advancing%20loss%20of%20tree%20cover%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcordis.europa.eu%2Farticle%2Fid%2F443056-when-forests-go-so-does-the-rain%5C%22%3Epotentially%20altered%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fmar%2F01%2Fscientists-prove-clear-correlation-between-deforestation-and-rainfall-levels%5C%22%3Erainfall%20patterns%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well.%20When%20they%20decided%20to%20plant%20above%20the%20floodplains%2C%20clearing%20and%20ploughing%20the%20land%2C%20digging%20canals%20to%20redirect%20water%20into%20these%20dry%20fields%2C%20they%20produced%20more%20food%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20but%20the%20deep%20tillage%20destroyed%20the%20topsoil%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F340088672_Soil_Salinity_of_Mesopotamia_and_the_Main_Drains%5C%22%3Eirrigation%20left%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fndrip.com%2Fsoil-salinity-and-field-flooding%2F%5C%22%3Esalt%20residues%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rendering%20the%20land%20fruitless%20after%20some%20years.%20Ironically%2C%20these%20townsfolk%20were%20now%20working%20%3Cem%3Emuch%3C%2Fem%3E%20harder%20than%20their%20foraging%20ancestors%20had%20ever%20done%2C%20yet%20were%20left%20with%20a%20narrower%2C%20less%20nutritive%20diet%20and%20a%20greater%20vulnerability%20to%20famine%2C%20as%20their%20mono-cropped%20fields%20fell%20increasingly%20to%20pests%20and%20blight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20penned%20more%20goats%2C%20sheep%2C%20and%20cattle%20inside%20their%20cities%2C%20but%20then%20fell%20victim%20to%20a%20rash%20of%20new%20zoonotic%20diseases.%20Archaeologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldcat.org%2Ftitle%2Fdaily-life-in-ancient-mesopotamia%2Foclc%2F38168335%5C%22%3EKaren%20Rhea%20Nemet-Nejat%3C%2Fa%3E%20mentions%20tuberculosis%2C%20typhoid%2C%20and%20smallpox%20that%20first%20passed%20into%20humans%20during%20this%20time.%20Political%20scientist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyalebooks.yale.edu%2Fbook%2F9780300240214%2Fagainst-the-grain%2F%5C%22%3EJames%20Scott%3C%2Fa%3E%20observes%20that%20such%20epidemics%20regularly%20drove%20entire%20settlements%20to%20collapse%2C%20through%20mass%20death%20and%20abandonment.%20Meanwhile%2C%20nearby%20meadows%20were%20denuded%20by%20overgrazing%2C%20rendered%20into%20dust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20farmers%20were%20working%20harder%20to%20keep%20their%20intensive%20subsistence%20program%20afloat%2C%20they%20yet%20grew%20entirely%20dependent%20upon%20their%20cultivated%20foods.%20Their%20attention%20turned%20away%20from%20broader%20ecosystem%20nurturance%20to%20focus%20on%20maximizing%20short-term%20productivity%20among%20their%20few%20domesticated%20species.%20Their%20foraging%20skills%20atrophied.%20They%20forgot%20the%20spirits%20of%20animals%20and%20trees%20to%20whom%20they%E2%80%99d%20once%20felt%20a%20meaningful%20kinship.%20Their%20ritual%20focus%20shifted%20skyward%2C%20as%20rain%20and%20weather%20now%20commanded%20their%20collective%20fate.%20These%20farmers%20were%20no%20longer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Efluidly%20adjusting%20their%20lifestyles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20social%20structures%20to%20fit%20the%20dictates%20of%20the%20land%2C%20as%20their%20foraging%20ancestors%20had%20once%20done.%20They%20now%20sought%20to%20reshape%20their%20environment%20to%20fit%20the%20dictates%20of%20their%20society%20and%20its%20dominant%20ideologies%2C%20which%20increasingly%20viewed%20urbanism%20and%20agriculture%20as%20superior%20to%20other%20ways%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArchaeologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fwhat-makes-civilization-9780199699421%3Fcc%3Dus%26lang%3Den%26%5C%22%3EDavid%20Wengrow%3C%2Fa%3E%20reminds%20us%20that%2C%20though%20the%20earliest%20Mesopotamian%20cities%20were%20already%20dependent%20upon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fasbbs.org%2Ffiles%2FASBBS2012V1%2FPDF%2FA%2FAlexanderW.pdf%5C%22%3Elong-distance%20trade%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20essential%20commodities%2C%20from%20wood%20to%20metal%20to%20stone%2C%20fiat%20money%20yet%20remained%20unknown.%20Grains%20and%20goods%20and%20metals%20were%20traded%20between%20cities%20or%20with%20nomadic%20pastoralist%20communities.%20Those%20mobile%20groups%20could%20ply%20trade%20between%20the%20cities%20and%20the%20hinterlands%2C%20where%20foraging%20communities%20continued%20to%20thrive%2C%20able%20to%20supply%20certain%20raw%20materials%20from%20forests%20or%20mountains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20within%20each%20city%2C%20markets%20and%20trade%20did%20not%20direct%20the%20economy.%20Rather%2C%20all%20lands%20and%20herds%20belonged%20to%20the%20deity%20residing%20in%20the%20central%20temple%2C%20and%20were%20communally%20worked.%20The%20needs%20and%20routines%20of%20daily%20life%20were%20disparately%20organised%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eth.mpg.de%2F4091237%2FGoody_Lecture_2015.pdf%5C%22%3Eseparate%20kinship%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20likely%20still%20based%20in%20networks%20of%20mutual%20aid%20that%20provisioned%20individuals.%20This%20city-wide%20joint%20tenureship%20of%20production%20with%20distributed%20governance%20functioned%20in%20service%20to%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20deity.%20Feeding%20the%20gods%20was%20understood%20to%20be%20the%20true%20purpose%20of%20agricultural%20labor%2C%20the%20ideological%20basis%20shaping%20their%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20reliance%20on%20cereal%20and%20animal%20farming%20was%20driving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F26748449%5C%22%3Ea%20commensurate%20reliance%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20complex%20processes%2C%20technologies%2C%20and%20social%20institutions.%20Families%20increasingly%20specialised%20in%20trades%2C%20developing%20new%20skills%20and%20knowledge%2C%20revising%20the%20social%20relationships%20and%20networks%20of%20obligation%20that%20would%20have%20defined%20their%20distributed%20gift%20economies.%20And%20as%2C%20over%20centuries%2C%20this%20technological%20and%20social%20complexity%20escalated%2C%20production%20and%20redistribution%20of%20provisions%20became%20increasingly%20driven%20and%20organised%20by%20the%20temple.%20The%20centralisation%20of%20goods%2C%20knowledge%2C%20and%20power%20intensified.%20Temple%20functionaries%20invented%20writing%20to%20administer%20these%20complex%20logistics%20of%20labour%2C%20production%2C%20and%20redistribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20changing%20social%20world%2C%20individuals%E2%80%99%20roles%20were%20narrowing%2C%20delineated%20by%20one%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20within%20the%20urban%20project%20of%20servicing%20the%20temple.%20Ritual%20specialists%E2%80%94priests%20and%20temple%20workers%2C%20scribes%2C%20and%20perhaps%20artisans%20who%20knew%20the%20magic%20of%20refining%20gemstones%20or%20forging%20copper%20used%20in%20ritual%E2%80%94increasingly%20commanded%20status.%20Familial%20inheritance%20of%20specialised%20knowledge%2C%20skills%2C%20and%20associated%20status%20was%20shaping%20the%20rise%20of%20differentiated%20social%20power.%20Eventually%2C%20low-status%20subjects%20came%20to%20be%20meagrely%20provisioned%20by%20the%20state%2C%20while%20hereditary%20elites%20began%20to%20claim%20exclusive%20rights%20to%20particular%20fields%20or%20ponds%2C%20acquiring%20private%20wealth.%20A%20family%20with%20means%20could%20handsomely%20gift%20a%20scribe%20to%20admit%20their%20son%20or%E2%80%94rarely%E2%80%94daughter%20into%20scribal%20school%2C%20a%20privilege%20securing%20them%20a%20higher%20position%20on%20the%20urban%20ladder.%20And%20as%20cities%20were%20increasingly%20sacked%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fpower-lines%2Fborder-walls-alliances-and-blurry-identities-nomadic-peoples-and-the-early-empire-287c4b6b881c%5C%22%3Enomadic%20raiders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20were%20beginning%20to%20command%20the%20hinterlands%2C%20warfare%20was%20also%20becoming%20a%20feature%20of%20urban%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20service%20of%20propitiating%20their%20deity%2C%20city%20rulers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aeaweb.org%2Fcontent%2Ffile%3Fid%3D20176%5C%22%3Estrove%20to%20maintain%20elite%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20a%20productive%20social%20edifice.%20They%20kept%20copper%2C%20silver%2C%20gold%2C%20lapis%20lazuli%2C%20carnelian%20and%20other%20magical%20ingredients%20flowing%20from%20distant%20cities%20and%20the%20hinterlands%20toward%20the%20temples%20to%20create%20and%20consecrate%20more%20divine%20statuary%20and%20ritual%20objects%E2%80%94effectively%20a%20system%20of%20hoarding%20in%20which%20the%20temple%20became%20the%20site%20of%20accrual.%20They%20provisioned%20meat%20to%20feed%20their%20deity%2C%20commissioned%20temples%2C%20city%20walls%2C%20irrigation%20canals%2C%20record-keeping%2C%20and%20more.%20All%20this%20required%20more%20workers%20and%20more%20grain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20overshooting%20their%20environmental%20limits%2C%20most%20cities%20collapsed%20within%20a%20few%20generations.%20Their%20people%20variously%20scattered%20to%20find%20place%20in%20other%20cities%20or%20to%20found%20new%20ones%E2%80%94or%20they%20dispersed%20among%20the%20roaming%20tribes%2C%20to%20become%20pastoralists%20or%20raiders.%20As%20it%20was%2C%20the%20main%20remedies%20left%20to%20avoid%20urban%20collapse%20were%20for%20cities%20also%20to%20raid%20their%20neighbors%2C%20stealing%20resources%2C%20treasure%2C%20and%20workers%3B%20to%20enslave%20nomads%20from%20the%20hinterlands%20for%20their%20labour%3B%20and%20to%20conquer%20new%20territories.%20It%20was%20in%20this%20context%20that%20some%20men%20ascended%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20kings%E2%80%94considered%20demigods%E2%80%94in%20Sumer%20around%202900%20BCE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20a%20few%20elites%20were%20able%20to%20co-opt%20the%20labour%20of%20armies%20of%20subordinates.%20Legions%20of%20men%20worked%20in%20the%20fields%2C%20while%20women%20of%20similar%20status%20sat%20indoors%2C%20grinding%20grain%20or%20spinning%20wool.%20These%20women%20were%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20control%20under%20such%20conditions%3B%20processing%20grain%20and%20raising%20children%20took%20up%20all%20their%20time%20and%20energy%2C%20while%20the%20changing%20configurations%20of%20social%20spaces%20had%20increasingly%20marginalised%20them%2C%20limiting%20their%20regular%20participation%20in%20public%20discourse.%20Men%20worked%20the%20plows%20and%20tended%20the%20herds%2C%20administered%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20waged%20war.%20Though%20some%20women%20still%20worked%20alongside%20men%20in%20the%20temples%20as%20priests%2C%20scribes%2C%20or%20sex%20workers%2C%20the%20broader%20social%2C%20cultural%2C%20and%20economic%20contributions%20of%20women%20were%20steadily%20being%20constrained%2C%20silenced%2C%20and%20devalued%20against%20the%20ascendent%20powers%20of%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometime%20after%202500%20BCE%2C%20semi-settled%20or%20fully%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifad.org%2Fen%2Fweb%2Flatest%2F-%2Fqa-shifting-cultivation%5C%22%3Esettled%20forager-gardeners%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20various%20sites%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2F10.1086%2F658900%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20Deccan%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20absorbing%20domesticated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2F10.1086%2F658900%5C%22%3Ecrops%20and%20animals%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20western%20Eurasia%20and%20later%20Africa%2C%20also%20hybridising%20local%20rices%20with%20eastern%20Eurasian%20strains.%20When%20city-states%20later%20began%20to%20arise%20on%20the%20peninsula%2C%20some%20communities%20fled%20their%20vicinity%2C%20adapting%20swidden%20to%20mountain%20geographies.%20Swidden%20remained%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Ftopics%2Fearth-and-planetary-sciences%2Fshifting-cultivation%5C%22%3Erelatively%20sustainable%3C%2Fa%3E%20lifeway%20for%20many%20Adivasi%20groups%20until%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.teriin.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-12%2FSatoyama_Book_Updated.pdf%5C%22%3Emodern%20times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20as%20official%20policies%20have%20restricted%20Adivasis%E2%80%99%20usage%20of%20their%20lands%2C%20fallowing%20periods%20are%20reduced%2C%20diminishing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Ftopics%2Fearth-and-planetary-sciences%2Fshifting-cultivation%5C%22%3Esustainability%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMalnutrition%20increasingly%20stalked%20the%20land%E2%80%94especially%20iron%20deficiency%2C%20which%20most%20acutely%20afflicts%20women%20of%20childbearing%20age.%20The%20masses%20were%20overworked%20and%20underfed%2C%20evident%20from%20the%20work-related%20injuries%20and%20malnourishment%20that%20marked%20their%20bones%E2%80%94absent%20from%20the%20bones%20of%20their%20foraging%20contemporaries%2C%20who%20lived%20outside%20the%20city%20walls.%20Their%20cereal-heavy%20diet%20promoted%20tooth%20decay.%20Crop%20blight%20or%20drought%20multiplied%20seasons%20of%20famine.%20As%20societies%20locked%20themselves%20into%20large-scale%20agricultural%20systems%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.1120177109%5C%22%3Ethey%20endured%20suffering%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20magnitudes%20unknown%20to%20nomadic%20foragers.%20And%20they%20died%20much%20younger.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20once%20Fertile%20Crescent%20was%20being%20incrementally%20transformed%20into%20a%20land%20of%20dust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20might%20recognise%20this%20path%20of%20decision-making%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Eprogress%20trap%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%2C%20in%20systems-theoretic%20parlance%2C%20a%20story%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFixes_that_fail%5C%22%3EFixes%20that%20Fail%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20devising%20complex%20solutions%20to%20problems%20which%20then%20cause%20more%20complex%20problems%2C%20to%20be%20answered%20by%20increasingly%20complex%20solutions%2C%20until%20the%20system%20is%20so%20rigid%20and%20over-leveraged%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20vulnerable%20to%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUrban-scale%2C%20fixed-field%2C%20cereal%20farming%20independently%20emerged%20also%20in%20eastern%20Asia%20and%20Central%20America.%20From%20these%20origins%2C%20agricultural%2C%20statist%20civilisations%E2%80%94led%20by%20similar%20compulsive%20and%20propulsive%20logic%E2%80%94began%20spreading%20themselves%20across%20the%20continents.%20As%20they%20grew%2C%20they%20cleared%20forests%2C%20altered%20landscapes%2C%20destroyed%20ecosystems.%20They%20forcibly%20displaced%20or%20absorbed%20nomadic%20peoples%20and%20conquered%20rivals%2C%20as%20their%20cultural%20narratives%20evolved%20to%20justify%20and%20further%20compel%20this%20way%20of%20life.%20Conquest%20itself%20became%20an%20ideology%20and%20an%20economic%20paradigm.%20By%20five%20hundred%20years%20ago%2C%20this%20process%20took%20on%20a%20virulent%20new%20form%20in%20European%20colonialism%2C%20made%20more%20zealously%20extractivist%20by%20the%20emerging%20ideologies%20of%20capitalism%20and%20then%20accelerated%20and%20intensified%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20combustible%20fossils.%20It%20was%20this%20juggernaut%20that%20spread%20agricultural%20and%20then%20industrial%20statism%20farther%20and%20faster%20around%20the%20globe%2C%20finally%20carrying%20it%20to%20the%20last%20corners%20of%20the%20Earth%20only%20within%20the%20past%20few%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F3quarksdaily.com%2F3quarksdaily%2F2021%2F07%2Fof-gods-and-men-and-human-destiny.html%5C%22%3Estories%20from%20ancient%20Sumer%3C%2Fa%3E%20already%20encompassed%20beliefs%20and%20values%20that%20we%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F3quarksdaily.com%2F3quarksdaily%2F2020%2F10%2Ftales-from-a-changing-world.html%5C%22%3Erecognise%20as%20basal%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20our%20modern%20mythologies%3A%20They%20already%20valorised%20urban%20life%20and%20statism%20above%20all%20other%20sociopolitical%20arrangements.%20They%20already%20accepted%20social%20inequity%20and%20believed%20elite%20concentrations%20of%20power%20were%20divinely%20justified.%20They%20celebrated%20the%20dominance%20or%20triumph%20of%20powerful%20male%20individuals%20over%20multitudes%20as%20virtuous%20and%20heroic.%20They%20elevated%20deities%20conceived%20in%20the%20human%20image%20and%20claimed%20humans%20were%20a%20special%20creation%20of%20god%2C%20intended%20to%20dominate%20the%20non-human%20world%2C%20granted%20sanction%20even%20to%20destroy%20it%20in%20fostering%20human%20power.%20How%20distant%20were%20these%20stories%20from%20those%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fmodern-myths-of-prehistory%5C%22%3Eforaging%20ancestors%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20contemporaries!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20such%20notions%20yet%20remain%20substrate%20to%20industrial%20age%20mythologies%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20in%20common%20presumptions%20about%20human%20entitlements%20to%20%E2%80%98nature%2C%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20conceived%20as%20something%20separate%20and%20inferior%20to%20humankind.%20Or%20in%20our%20imagining%20the%20human%20experience%20as%20exceptional%2C%20nearer%20to%20the%20divine.%20That%20human%20potential%20is%20godlike%20and%20limitless.%20They%20resonate%20in%20the%20belief%20that%20patriarchy%20and%20other%20modes%20of%20sociopolitical%20inequity%20are%20inevitable.%20And%20that%20statist%20institutions%20are%20truly%20the%20%3Cem%3Etelos%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20pinnacle%20of%20human%20achievement%E2%80%94indeed%2C%20of%20all%20creation.%20They%20inspire%20mythologies%20of%20endless%20economic%20growth%20and%20undergird%20our%20presumptions%20that%20hierarchy%2C%20competition%2C%20and%20conquest%20characterise%20an%20inescapable%20and%20even%20divine%20human%20destiny%E2%80%94a%20colossal%20folly%20that%E2%80%99s%20now%20hurtling%20us%20toward%20our%20possible%20annihilation.%20This%20is%20the%20topic%20I%20pick%20up%20in%20the%20next%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709789442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07104838%2FIMG_2962.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-agricultural-revolution-an-alternate-telling%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20%E2%80%98Agricultural%20Revolution%2C%E2%80%99%20regularly%20presented%20as%20a%20grand%20origin%20myth%20of%20modern%20civilisation%2C%20was%20neither%20a%20swift%20nor%20serendipitous%20innovation%20eagerly%20embraced%20by%20all.%20Nor%20would%20it%20herald%20a%20giant%20leap%20in%20the%20social%2C%20healthful%2C%20and%20creative%20prospects%20of%20humanity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-agricultural-revolution-an-alternate-telling%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple's%20car%20at%20one%20point%20replaced%20the%20steering%20wheel%20with%20an%20Xbox-like%20controller%20for%20when%20its%20self-driving%20couldn't%20cut%20it%3A%20Bloomberg%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224143%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apple%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20talks%20to%20an%20employee%20at%20a%20solar%20park%20in%20Hanstholm%2C%20Denmark.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F