p%3BK%20administration%20rejected%20the%20Hurriyat%20leader%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%98illegally%E2%80%99%20detained%20at%20his%20Srinagar%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20cited%20over%20two%20dozen%20instances%2C%20including%20a%20recent%20visit%20to%20New%20Delhi%2C%20when%20Mirwaiz%20was%20reportedly%20allowed%20to%20attend%20social%20and%20religious%20functions%20and%20also%20to%20medical%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%E2%80%99s%20reply%20came%20in%20response%20to%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20through%20which%20Mirwaiz%20had%20challenged%20his%20%E2%80%9Carbitrary%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%E2%80%9D%20detention%20in%20the%20high%20court%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20on%20Wednesday%20set%20March%2014%20as%20the%20next%20date%20of%20hearing%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20petition%2C%20Mirwaiz%20had%20alleged%20that%20security%20forces%20have%20detained%20him%20since%20August%205%2C%202019%20with%20armoured%20vehicles%20along%20with%20police%20and%20paramilitary%20forces%20deployed%20at%20the%20main%20gate%20of%20his%20home%20in%20Srinagar%E2%80%99s%20Nigeen%20locality%20and%20that%20they%20prevent%20him%20from%20coming%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMirwaiz%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20chief%20cleric%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20delivered%20sermons%20on%20important%20religious%20occasions%20at%20the%20Jamia%20Masjid%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20oldest%20mosque%2C%20which%20is%20located%20in%20in%20Srinagar%20and%20where%20congregational%20prayers%20have%20been%20largely%20banned%20by%20authorities%20amid%20fears%20over%20the%20breakdown%20of%20law%20and%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20counsel%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20the%20allegation%2C%20asserting%20that%20there%20was%20no%20detention%20order%20against%20Mirwaiz%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnone%20of%20%5Bhis%5D%20legal%2C%20constitutional%20or%20statutory%20rights%E2%80%9D%20were%20being%20violated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20assassination%20of%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20father%20Moulana%20Mohammad%20Farooq%20on%20May%2021%2C%201990%2C%20the%20counsel%20told%20the%20high%20court%20that%20the%20Hurriyat%20leader%20was%20%E2%80%9Cadvised%E2%80%9D%20to%20restrict%20his%20movement%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20some%20time%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Coverall%20security%20scenario%E2%80%9D%20in%20Srinagar%20after%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20informed%20by%20the%20state%20that%20Mirwaiz%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20well-known%20and%20respected%20religious%20head%20and%20pubic%20figure%E2%80%9D%20whose%20residence%20was%20located%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Csensitive%20and%20strategic%E2%80%9D%20area%20of%20Srinagar%20flanked%20by%20the%20Hazratbal%20shrine%2C%20where%20thousands%20of%20Muslim%20devotees%20converge%20on%20religious%20occasions%3B%20the%20volatile%20National%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20which%20has%20witnessed%20communal%20clashes%20between%20students%3B%20and%20the%20upscale%20Nigeen%20Club.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20visualising%20the%20perceived%20threat%20perception%20of%20the%20petitioner%20in%20the%20set%20of%20circumstances%2C%20the%20agencies%20cannot%20afford%20to%20take%20even%20a%20slightest%20risk%20in%20curtailing%20the%20deployment%20of%20the%20security%20personnel%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20counsel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20threat%20perception%20of%20the%20petitioner%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%20under%20any%20circumstance%20which%20makes%20it%20expedient%20to%20deploy%20police%20contingents%20outside%20his%20house.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20also%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20Mirwaiz%20was%20%E2%80%9Cadvised%20not%20to%20visit%20public%20and%20large%20gatherings%20which%20was%20in%20his%20own%20interest%20and%20also%20in%20compliance%20to%20SOP%20regarding%20COVID-19%E2%80%9D%20following%20the%20outbreak%20of%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20there%20has%20not%20been%20any%20specific%20restraint%20or%20alleged%20detention%20of%20the%20petitioner%2C%20as%20he%20has%20%5Boff%5D%20and%20on%20visited%20his%20relatives%20and%20other%20places.%20The%20petitioner%20has%20recently%20also%20offered%20namaz%20%5Bprayers%5D%20at%20Jamia%20Masjid%20and%20delivered%20sermons%20also%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20counsel%20said%2C%20terming%20the%20petition%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmisconceived%E2%80%9D%20and%20saying%20it%20%E2%80%9Cdeserves%20to%20be%20dismissed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20and%20paramilitary%20forces%20are%20deployed%20in%20the%20Nigeen%20area%20for%20the%20security%20of%20the%20non-local%20staff%20and%20students%20of%20the%20two%20leading%20educational%20institutions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20safety%20of%20migrant%20workers%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20have%20become%20victims%20of%20targeted%20attacks%20by%20militants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20vicinity%20around%20where%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20house%20is%20located%20is%20dominated%20as%20a%20preventive%20measure%20so%20as%20to%20avoid%20any%20terrorist%20activity%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20to%20foil%20any%20attempt%20of%20anti-national%20elements%20to%20disrupt%20peace%20and%20public%20order%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20state%20counsel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccusing%20Mirwaiz%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconcealing%20and%20suppressing%20the%20material%20facts%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20counsel%20cited%20official%20records%20of%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20instances%20when%20the%20moderate%20Hurriyat%20leader%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20attended%20social%20and%20religious%20functions%20besides%20medical%20emergencies%20since%20February%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hurriyat%20leader%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20free%20man%20who%20on%20and%20off%20visits%20doctors%2C%20relatives%20and%20attend(s)%20other%20religious%20activities%20at%20his%20will%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20court%20was%20informed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20petitioner%20has%20neither%20been%20detained%20nor%20has%20his%20freedom%20been%20jeopardised.%20The%20police%20deployment%E2%80%A6is%20purely%20for%20safety%20and%20security%20purpose%20and%20as%20a%20preventive%20measure%20so%20as%20to%20foil%20any%20attempt%20of%20anti-national%20elements%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20counsel%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709780337000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22212959%2FThe-Wire-16.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmirwaizs-movements-restricted-due-to-perceived-threat-from-terrorists-jk-admin-tells-hc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20administration%20rejected%20the%20moderate%20Hurriyat%20leader's%20allegation%20that%20he%20is%20being%20'arbitrarily'%20and%20'illegally'%20detained%20since%20August%205%2C%202019.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmirwaizs-movements-restricted-due-to-perceived-threat-from-terrorists-jk-admin-tells-hc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Michael%20Jackson%20Biopic%20Adds%20Laura%20Harrier%20as%20Pioneering%20Music%20Exec%20Suzanne%20de%20Passe%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709780221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Flaura-harrier-1.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D562%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235932899%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CMichael%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20splashy%20forthcoming%20biopic%20about%20Michael%20Jackson%20from%20director%20Antoine%20Fuqua%2C%20has%20added%20actor%20Laura%20Harrier%20in%20a%20key%20role.%20Harrier%2C%20of%20%E2%80%9CBlacKkKlansman%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CSpider-man%3A%20Homecoming%E2%80%9D%20fame%2C%20will%20portray%20pioneering%20female%20music%20executive%20Suzanne%20de%20Passe%20in%20the%20Lionsgate%20project.%20De%20Passe%20was%20a%20creative%20assistant%20to%20Motown%20founder%20Berry%20Gordy%2C%20and%20is%20credited%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Varietymattdonnelly%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fmichael-jackson-biopic-laura-harrier-suzanne-de-passe-1235932899%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fmichael-jackson-biopic-laura-harrier-suzanne-de-passe-1235932899%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fmichael-jackson-biopic-laura-harrier-suzanne-de-passe-1235932899%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Early%20Europeans%20Made%20Their%20Way%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Exotic'%20East%20After%20Learning%20of%20its%20Riches%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06175937%2F20.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20European%20expansion%20was%20not%20a%20development%20that%20grew%20from%20%E2%80%93%20so%20to%20speak%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98internal%20causes%E2%80%99.%20Quite%20to%20the%20contrary%2C%20it%20was%20the%20reaction%20to%20a%20mighty%20challenge%20which%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20had%20already%20been%20tempting%20the%20Occident%20for%20no%20less%20than%20two%20thousand%20years%2C%20tantalisingly%20rousing%20a%20certain%20predatory%20mentality%20among%20the%20Europeans%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20%E2%80%94%20Schmidt%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEuropeans%20began%20to%20wake%20up%20to%20the%20reality%20of%20Asia%20in%20a%20much%20more%20tangible%20fashion%20in%20the%20thirteenth%20century%2C%20when%20Marco%20Polo%E2%80%99s%20travel%20accounts%20began%20to%20be%20disseminated%20in%20Europe.%20The%20thirteenth%20century%20had%20already%20seen%20Europe%20opening%20up%20in%20a%20number%20of%20ways.%20For%20example%2C%20this%20was%20the%20century%20in%20which%20the%20great%20fairs%20of%20the%20Champagne%20country%2C%20today%20in%20France%2C%20began%20to%20be%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20large-scale%20exchange%20of%20the%20products%20of%20north%20and%20south%20Europe%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20the%20place%20where%20traders%20from%20around%20Europe%20could%20come%20to%20purchase%20the%20goods%20of%20the%20eastern%20lands%20that%20were%20being%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20Italian%20merchants.%20In%20the%20same%20century%2C%20a%20Jewish%20rabbi%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Benjamin%20from%20the%20Spanish%20city%20of%20Tudela%2C%20set%20out%20on%20his%20travels%20around%20the%20Mediterranean.%20He%20focused%20on%20identifying%20the%20cities%20which%20still%20had%20a%20large%20Jewish%20population%20%E2%80%93%20and%20he%20found%20quite%20a%20few!%20And%20as%20I%20said%20earlier%2C%20one%20place%20that%20he%20mentioned%2C%20the%20only%20one%20outside%20the%20Mediterranean%20region%2C%20lay%20on%20the%20Malabar%20coast.%20The%20Crusades%20had%20started%20over%20a%20century%20earlier%2C%20and%20warrior%20knights%20like%20the%20Knights%20Templar%20had%20already%20established%20themselves%20as%20an%20important%20group%20across%20Europe.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20century%2C%20the%20fourth%20crusade%2C%20which%20was%20supposed%20to%20attack%20Egypt%2C%20attacked%20Byzantium%20instead.%20Through%20all%20of%20this%2C%20the%20Italian%20cities%20of%20Venice%20and%20Genoa%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20continued%20their%20trade%20across%20the%20Mediterranean%2C%20to%20procure%20the%20goods%20of%20Asia.%20Venetian%20networks%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20included%20things%20as%20diverse%20as%20the%20trade%20in%20wine%20and%20spices%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20regular%20postal%20service%20between%20Venice%20and%20Constantinople.%20This%20was%20something%20that%20the%20king%20of%20Persia%20considered%20so%20important%20that%20in%201320%20he%20granted%20the%20Venetian%20couriers%20the%20freedom%20to%20travel%20throughout%20his%20dominions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20another%20level%2C%20too%2C%20knowledge%20of%20the%20lands%20of%20the%20east%20impinged%20on%20Europe%2C%20through%20the%20Mongol%20invasions.%20The%20wealthy%20and%20%E2%80%98exotic%E2%80%99%20east%20had%20always%20been%20part%20of%20the%20European%20imaginaire.%20But%20now%2C%20Europe%20began%20to%20realise%20that%20the%20eastern%20lands%20were%20not%20just%20fabulous%2C%20fabulously%20wealthy%20or%20imagined%2C%20but%20real%2C%20really%20wealthy%20and%20probably%20really%20dangerous!%20The%20eastern%20lands%20were%20still%20%E2%80%98fabulous%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20were%20now%20becoming%20more%20tangible%2C%20and%20this%20tangibility%20had%2C%20at%20its%20core%2C%20the%20range%20of%20goods%20that%20were%20available.%20Crusaders%20who%20went%20through%20Venice%20or%20through%20Constantinople%20on%20their%20way%20to%20the%20Holy%20Land%20began%20to%20see%2C%20in%20the%20markets%20of%20Constantinople%20and%20further%20east%2C%20products%20that%20were%20not%20visible%20in%20Europe.%20Even%20the%20Mongols%2C%20a%20highly%20mobile%20and%20warlike%20force%2C%20who%20according%20to%20reports%20had%20only%20one%20large%20city%20in%20their%20dominions%2C%20dealt%20in%20gold%2C%20which%20was%20still%20limited%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20314px)%2085vw%2C%20314px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06150155%2FEmpires-of-the-Sea_front-cover.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22314%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06150155%2FEmpires-of-the-Sea_front-cover.jpg%20740w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06150155%2FEmpires-of-the-Sea_front-cover-185x300.jpg%20185w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06150155%2FEmpires-of-the-Sea_front-cover-631x1024.jpg%20631w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700420%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22509%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERadhika%20Seshan%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EEmpires%20of%20the%20Sea%3A%20A%20Human%20History%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPan%20Macmillan%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20dimension%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20Crusading%20Knights%2C%20particularly%20the%20Knights%20Templar.%20While%20the%20wealth%20that%20they%20accumulated%20may%20have%20increased%20in%20size%20along%20with%20the%20stories%20they%20told%2C%20they%20were%20all%20undoubtedly%20based%20in%20fact.%20The%20east%20acquired%20a%20materiality%20that%20fed%20into%20the%20fables%20of%20the%20fabulous%20east%20and%20these%20stories%20now%20started%20being%20fleshed%20out%20with%20eyewitness%20accounts.%20Finally%2C%20tales%20began%20to%20circulate%20in%20Europe%20about%20a%20priest%20king%20named%20Prester%20John.%20These%20stories%20had%20originated%20in%20the%20twelfth%20century%20but%20began%20to%20spread%20much%20more%20in%20the%20following%20century.%20Legend%20has%20it%20that%20Prester%20John%20was%20a%20Christian%20king%2C%20who%20ruled%20over%20a%20fabulously%20wealthy%20%E2%80%98eastern%E2%80%99%20land%2C%20but%20whose%20kingdom%20was%20now%20surrounded%20by%20%E2%80%98infidels%20and%20pagans%E2%80%99.%20He%20was%20reported%20to%20have%20written%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Pope%2C%20appealing%20for%20help%2C%20and%20in%20return%2C%20promised%20that%20he%20would%20welcome%20all%20good%20Christians%2C%20who%20could%20then%20trade%20within%20his%20territories.%20Stories%20about%20Prester%20John%E2%80%99s%20land%20mentioned%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20size%20of%20his%20kingdom%20and%20its%20wealth%2C%20displayed%20most%20clearly%20in%20his%20people%20eating%20off%20plates%20made%20of%20gold%20and%20silver%2C%20and%20of%20jewels%20being%20worn%20by%20everyone.%20His%20kingdom%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20somewhere%20in%20the%20east%3B%20and%20so%2C%20travels%20began%20in%20search%20of%20this%20promised%20land.%20Marco%20Polo%E2%80%99s%20account%2C%20in%20which%20he%20included%20a%20note%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98land%20of%20Prester%20John%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20its%20concrete%20descriptions%20of%20the%20wealth%20of%20China%2C%20gave%20added%20fillip%20to%20this%20quest.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20centuries%2C%20the%20search%20for%20Prester%20John%20informed%20many%20of%20the%20travels%20to%20the%20east%3B%20and%20finally%2C%20this%20search%20was%20narrowed%20down%20to%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20world%2C%20including%20Central%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrester%20John%20was%20first%20located%20in%20Malabar%2C%20where%20it%20was%20said%20St%20Thomas%20had%20been%20martyred%20and%20his%20bones%20were%20buried.%20The%20martyrdom%20took%20place%20in%20the%20modern%20city%20of%20Chennai%2C%20and%20the%20relics%20were%20supposedly%20taken%20to%20Edessa%20and%20later%20to%20Italy%2C%20but%20Malabar%20was%20fixed%20as%20the%20location%20of%20Prester%20John%E2%80%99s%20kingdom.%20As%20knowledge%20about%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20Christian%20community%20in%20Malabar%20spread%2C%20a%20bishop%20named%20Jordanus%20was%20sent%20to%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20bishopric%20of%20Quilon%20in%20the%20fourteenth%20century.%20By%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20fifteenth%20century%2C%20Prester%20John%E2%80%99s%20kingdom%20had%20moved%20to%20Ethiopia%3B%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20was%20also%20located%20in%20Central%20Asia%20and%2C%20a%20little%20later%2C%20in%20Japan!%20The%20one%20thing%20that%20remained%20constant%2C%20was%20that%20he%20and%20his%20kingdom%20were%20always%20located%20with%2C%20or%20within%2C%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20world.%20And%20so%2C%20for%20Europe%2C%20India%20(and%20Asia)%20became%20even%20more%20the%20land%20of%20plenty.%20All%20they%20had%20to%20do%2C%20was%20get%20to%20this%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexcerpt-why-indias-social-development-indicators-lag-behind-its-neighbours%5C%22%3EExcerpt%3A%20Why%20India%E2%80%99s%20Social%20Development%20Indicators%20Lag%20Behind%20its%20Neighbours%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20the%20thirteenth%20and%20fifteenth%20centuries%2C%20as%20more%20stories%20of%20this%20fabulous%20land%20spread%20and%20as%20more%20accurate%20sources%20of%20information%20also%20began%20to%20find%20their%20way%20into%20Europe%2C%20the%20fascination%20with%20these%20eastern%20lands%20grew.%20The%20accounts%20of%20travellers%20like%20Marco%20Polo%20in%20the%20thirteenth%20century%2C%20John%20Marignolli%20in%20the%20fourteenth%20century%2C%20and%20Nicolo%20Conti%20in%20the%20fifteenth%20century%2C%20all%20helped%20in%20the%20dissemination%20of%20factual%20knowledge%20about%20the%20riches%20of%20the%20east.%20Linked%20to%20the%20fifteenth-%20century%20voyages%20of%20exploration%2C%20this%20combination%20of%20fact%20and%20fiction%20made%20access%20to%20these%20lands%20even%20more%20desirable.%20In%201453%2C%20came%20the%20fall%20of%20Constantinople%20to%20the%20Ottoman%20troops.%20One%20immediate%20result%20of%20this%20was%20the%20(temporary)%20closure%20of%20the%20trade%20routes%20that%20led%20east%2C%20which%20meant%2C%20if%20nothing%20else%2C%20a%20shortage%20of%20pepper%2C%20the%20spice%20most%20demanded%20in%20Europe.%20When%20trade%20resumed%20(which%20it%20did%2C%20quite%20soon)%2C%20the%20traders%20found%20that%20customs%20duties%20and%20assorted%20tolls%20and%20taxes%20were%20now%20collected%20much%20more%20strictly%20than%20had%20been%20the%20case.%20One%20consequence%20was%20naturally%20an%20increase%20in%20prices%2C%20which%2C%20allied%20to%20the%20already%20prevailing%20suspicions%20of%20the%20Ottoman%20bureaucracy%2C%20made%20the%20search%20for%20a%20route%20that%20bypassed%20the%20Ottoman%20empire%20altogether%2C%20even%20more%20urgent.%20This%20was%20linked%20to%20the%20voyages%20of%20exploration%20that%20had%20already%20begun%2C%20and%20now%20gathered%20momentum.%20It%20was%20the%20age%20of%20legendary%20explorers%20%E2%80%93%20Bartolomeo%20Dias%2C%20Amerigo%20Vespucci%2C%20Christopher%20Columbus%2C%20Vasco%20da%20Gama%20and%20many%20more.%20In%201494%2C%20by%20the%20Treaty%20of%20Tordesillas%2C%20it%20was%20declared%20that%20Papal%20sanction%20for%20discovery%20and%20conquest%20had%20been%20given%20to%20Spain%20and%20Portugal%2C%20so%20all%20lands%20west%20of%20the%20line%20of%20the%20treaty%20were%20to%20be%20for%20Spain%2C%20and%20those%20to%20the%20east%20for%20Portugal.%20The%20treaty%20was%20observed%20more%20in%20its%20absence%20than%20its%20observance%3B%20but%20Portugal%20got%20(in%20some%20ways)%20the%20better%20part%20of%20the%20bargain%2C%20because%20to%20the%20east%20lay%20the%20wealthy%20lands%20of%20the%20Indies.%20Portugal%E2%80%99s%20expansion%20in%20this%20direction%20was%20now%20with%20the%20sanction%20of%20the%20Church.%20One%20fallout%20of%20this%20has%20been%20the%20oft-quoted%20statement%20of%20the%20Portuguese%20empire%20being%20created%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98sword%20and%20Bible%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06180143%2F9.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06180143%2F9.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06180143%2F9-300x188.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06180143%2F9-1024x640.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700454%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Voyage%20to%20Calicut%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20from%20a%20sixteenth-century%20tapestry%20illustrating%20Vasco%20da%20Gama%E2%80%99s%20departure%20from%20Portugal%20and%20arrival%20at%20Calicut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20outward%20movement%20from%20Europe%20in%20the%20fifteenth%20century%20did%20not%2C%20at%20least%20initially%2C%20involve%20any%20marked%20changes%20in%20ship%20technology.%20Such%20technology%20was%20probably%20at%20about%20the%20same%20level%20in%20both%20Asia%20and%20Europe%20at%20this%20time.%20What%20did%20happen%20in%20Europe%2C%20was%20a%20more%20coherent%20understanding%20of%20the%20different%20wind%20systems%20that%20prevailed%20in%20the%20different%20regions%20of%20Europe%2C%20Asia%20and%20Africa.%20Therefore%2C%20as%20a%20corollary%2C%20a%20logical%20and%20planned%20method%20of%20utilising%20these%20wind%20systems%20to%20travel%20more%20efficiently%20from%20one%20place%20to%20another%20transpired.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20this%20period%20saw%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20more%20coherent%20and%20possibly%20universal%20system%20of%20knowledge.%20By%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20fifteenth%20century%2C%20Portuguese%20mariners%20had%20learnt%20the%20wind%20systems%20operating%20off%20the%20Saharan%20coast%2C%20and%20then%20began%20their%20moves%20both%20further%20south%20along%20the%20African%20coast%20and%20across%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20to%20South%20America.%20In%20the%201430s%2C%20Madeira%20and%20the%20Azores%20islands%20were%20settled%20by%20the%20Portuguese%2C%20and%20in%201488%2C%20Bartolomeu%20Dias%20rounded%20the%20Cape%20of%20Good%20Hope.%20Then%20came%20Vasco%20da%20Gama%2C%20who%20reached%20Malabar%20in%201498%2C%20and%20returned%20to%20Portugal%20in%201499.%20I%20must%20emphasise%20that%20such%20knowledge%20was%20not%20restricted%20to%20the%20Portuguese%20and%20the%20Spanish%2C%20and%20was%20shared%20among%20many%20people%2C%20as%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20Piri%20Reis%20map.%20This%2C%20a%20map%20created%20in%20the%20Ottoman%20empire%20early%20in%20the%20sixteenth%20century%20and%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20first%20world%20map%2C%20has%20the%20outlines%20of%20South%20America%20drawn%20in%20it.%20Interestingly%2C%20this%20was%20also%20a%20region%20to%20which%20the%20Ottoman%20ships%20never%20sailed.%20Piri%20Reis%20seems%20to%20have%20drawn%20upon%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20Portuguese%20and%20Spanish%20mariners%20who%20had%20visited%20this%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdam%20Smith%2C%20in%20the%20eighteenth%20century%2C%20stated%20that%20the%20discoveries%20of%20America%20and%20the%20sea%20route%20around%20the%20Cape%20of%20Good%20Hope%20to%20India%2C%20were%20the%20%E2%80%98two%20greatest%20and%20most%20important%20events%20recorded%20in%20the%20history%20of%20mankind%E2%80%99.%20The%20Indian%20historian%2C%20Ashin%20Das%20Gupta%2C%20has%20however%20said%20that%20the%20arrival%20of%20Vasco%20da%20Gama%20on%20Indian%20shores%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98landmark%20wherein%20we%20do%20not%20quite%20know%20what%20it%20marks%E2%80%99.%20So%2C%20what%20did%20these%20discoveries%20mark%3F%20The%20general%20tendency%20has%20often%20been%20to%20talk%20of%20the%20proceedings%2C%20from%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20Portuguese%20in%20the%20sixteenth%20century%20till%20the%20establishment%20of%20British%20colonial%20rule%20in%20the%20eighteenth%20century%2C%20as%20a%20seamless%20process%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20takeover%20by%20the%20Europeans%2C%20with%20the%20Indians%20being%20passive%20onlookers%2C%20or%20sometimes%20even%20active%20participants%2C%20for%20reasons%20of%20personal%20aggrandisement.%20Linked%20to%20this%20is%20another%20idea%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20Europeans%20succeeded%20because%20they%20were%20masters%20of%20the%20sea%20and%2C%20from%20there%2C%20made%20their%20way%20to%20the%20land%2C%20while%20the%20Indians%20restricted%20themselves%20to%20land%20alone.%20Indians%2C%20lacking%20knowledge%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20sea%2C%20ended%20up%20losing%20both%20land%20and%20sea.%20Such%20statements%2C%20though%20unfortunately%20widely%20accepted%20still%2C%20are%20ahistorical%2C%20for%20they%20are%20chronologically%20and%20factually%20inaccurate.%20The%20reality%20was%20nowhere%20near%20as%20effortless%20as%20it%20is%20made%20out%20to%20be.%20So%2C%20what%20exactly%20changed%20and%20over%20how%20much%20time%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPublished%20from%20%E2%80%98Empires%20of%20the%20Sea%3A%20A%20Human%20History%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20World%E2%80%99%20with%20permission%20from%20the%20publisher.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERadhika%20Seshan%20retired%20as%20Professor%20and%20Head%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20History%2C%20Savitribai%20Phule%20Pune%20University.%20She%20is%20the%20author%20and%20editor%20of%20several%20books%2C%20including%20Narratives%2C%20Routes%20and%20Intersections%20in%20Pre-Modern%20Asia%2C%20Trade%20and%20Politics%20on%20the%20Coromandel%20Coast%3A%20Seventeenth%20and%20Early%20Eighteenth%20Centuries%20and%20Medieval%20India%3A%20Problems%20and%20Possibilities.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709779460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06175937%2F20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-early-europeans-made-their-way-to-the-exotic-east-after-learning-of-its-riches%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20book%20on%20the%20maritime%20history%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20suggests%20that%20prevailing%20notions%20of%20European%20superiority%20of%20the%20seas%20can%20be%20challenged.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-early-europeans-made-their-way-to-the-exotic-east-after-learning-of-its-riches%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20will%20be%20global%20'force%20for%20peace'%3A%20Foreign%20minister%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709779205000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108282334%2Cimgsize-513142.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F