%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20and%20India%20Reiterate%20Call%20for%20Justice%20on%20Terror%20Attacks%2C%20Silent%20on%20Pannun%20Allegations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06235340%2FIndia-and-US-n-A-2.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20United%20States%20and%20India%20on%20Wednesday%20(March%206)%20reiterated%20the%20call%20for%20justice%20for%20the%20masterminds%20of%20the%2026%2F11%20Mumbai%20and%20Pathankot%20Air%20Force%20Base%20terror%20attacks.%20However%2C%20both%20countries%20maintained%20public%20silence%20regarding%20any%20discussion%20of%20the%20allegations%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20assassinate%20a%20Sikh%20American-Canadian%20lawyer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20senior%20officials%20from%20India%20and%20the%20United%20States%20took%20part%20in%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20Counterterrorism%20Joint%20Working%20Group%20and%20Designations%20Dialogue%20at%20Washington.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F37682%2FJoint_Statement_of_the_20th_US_India_Counterterrorism_Joint_Working_Group_CTJWG_and_6th_Designations_Dialogue%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20joint%20statement%20issued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20after%20the%20meeting%20stated%20that%20both%20countries%20%E2%80%9Ccalled%20for%20the%20perpetrators%20of%20the%2026%2F11%20Mumbai%20and%20Pathankot%20terrorist%20attacks%20to%20be%20brought%20to%20justice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20also%20called%20for%20concerted%20action%20against%20all%20terrorist%20groups%2C%20including%20groups%20proscribed%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20(UNSC)%201267%20Sanctions%20Committee%2C%20such%20as%20al-Qaida%2C%20ISIS%2FDaesh%2C%20Lashkar-e-Tayyiba%20(LeT)%2C%20and%20Jaish-e-Mohammad%20(JeM)%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20statement%20mentioned%20that%20both%20sides%20%E2%80%9Cexchanged%20information%20regarding%20priorities%20and%20procedures%20for%20designating%20various%20terrorist%20entities%2Fgroups%20and%20individuals%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20and%20the%20United%20States%20have%20jointly%20submitted%20proposals%20to%20a%20UN%20Security%20Council%20committee%20for%20listing%20several%20Pakistan-based%20terrorists%20in%20the%20council%E2%80%99s%20sanctions%20list.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20most%20of%20them%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fchina-unsc-sanction-lashkar-e-taiba-shahid-mahmood%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eblocked%20by%20China%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20meeting%20also%20took%20place%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20US%20prosecutors%20accusing%20an%20unnamed%20Indian%20official%20for%20being%20the%20main%20mastermind%20in%20the%20foiled%20attempt%20to%20target%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20the%20general%20counsel%20for%20a%20proscribed%20group%20named%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20unsealed%20US%20indictment%20had%20also%20linked%20the%20conspiracy%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20Canada%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20set%20up%20a%20high-level%20committee%20to%20probe%20the%20US%20allegations%2C%20but%20there%20has%20been%20no%20public%20confirmation%20whether%20the%20investigation%20has%20been%20completed%20or%20is%20still%20ongoing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20joint%20statement%20did%20not%20mention%20whether%20the%20issue%20was%20brought%20up%20and%20there%20have%20been%20no%20additional%20remarks%20from%20either%20side%20on%20this%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709749488000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06235340%2FIndia-and-US-n-A-2.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fus-and-india-reiterate-call-for-justice-on-terror-attacks-silent-on-pannun-allegations%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indian%20and%20US%20officials%20in%20Washington%20also%20called%20for%20%E2%80%9Cconcerted%20action%20against%20all%20terrorist%20groups%E2%80%9D%2C%20including%20those%20proscribed%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20sanctions%20committee%2C%20such%20as%20al-Qaida%2C%20ISIS%2C%20Lashkar-e-Tayyiba%20and%20Jaish-e-Mohammad.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fus-and-india-reiterate-call-for-justice-on-terror-attacks-silent-on-pannun-allegations%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Glenn%20Saldanha%20announced%20resignation%20as%20chairman%20of%20Glenmark%20Life%20Sciences%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709749014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2018-11%2F20%2Ffull%2F1542728820-8123.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fglenn-saldanha-announced-resignation-as-chairman-of-glenmark-life-sciences-124030600944_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Glenmark%20Life%20Sciences%20Ltd%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20its%20Chairman%20Glenn%20Saldanha%20and%20non-executive%20director%20VS%20Mani%20have%20resigned%20following%20change%20in%20ownership%20of%20the%20company%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fglenn-saldanha-announced-resignation-as-chairman-of-glenmark-life-sciences-124030600944_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2F